obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42691)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42691&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Manipur Panchayati Raj`
  line `Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the State of Manipur excepting any area to which the Manipur (Hill`
  line `Areas) District Council Act, 1971 (Manipur Act 76 of 1971) or the Manipur (Village Authorities in Hill`
  line `Areas) Act, 1956 (Manipur Act 80 of 1956) extends, or which has been or may hereafter be declared as,`
  line `or included in, a municipality under any law for the time being in force, or which has been or may`
  line `hereafter be declared as, or included in a cantonment under the Cantonment Act, 1924 (2 of 1924).`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 23rd April, 1994, vide notification No. S.O. 328(E), dated 23rd April, 1994, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42692)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42692&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha" means an Adhyaksha and a Up-Adhyakhsa of a Zilla`
  line `Parishad elected under section 54 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means Chairperson of a Standing Committee of a Zilla Parishad or a Gram`
  line `Panchayat, as the case may be, constituted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chief Executive Officer" means the Chief Executive Officer of a Zilla Parishad appointed`
  line `under section 75 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of the Government in the Development and`
  line `Panchayati Raj or such other person as may be appointed by the State Government to exercise the`
  line `powers of a Commissioner under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "district" means the revenue district;`
  line
  line `(f) "Deputy Commissioner" means the Deputy Commissioner of District;`
  line
  line `(g) "Government" means the State Government of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(h) "Gram Sabha" means a body consisting of persons registered in the electoral rolls relating to a`
  line `village comprised within the area of the Panchayat at the village level;`
  line
  line `(i) "Gram Panchayat" means the Gram Panchayat constituted under the Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "Official Gazette" means the Manipur Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "Panchayat" means a Gram Panchayat and a Zilla Parishad constituted under the provisions of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Panchayat area" means the territorial area of a Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(m) "population" means the population as ascertained at the last preceding census of which the`
  line `relevant figures have been published,`
  line
  line `(n) "Pradhan" means a Pradhan of a Gram Panchayat elected under section 21 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under the Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "Secretary" means the Secretary of a Gram Panchayat appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(q) "Standing Committee" means a Standing Committee constituted by a Zilla Parishad or a Gram`
  line `Panchayat under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "Up-Pradhan" means a Up-Pradhan of a Gram Panchayat elected under section 24 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) "village" means a village specified by the Governor by public notification to be a village for`
  line `the purpose of this Act and includes a group of villages so specified; and`
  line
  line `(t) "Zilla Parishad" means a Zilla Parishad of a district constituted under section 48 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42693)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Membership of Gram Sabha and disqualification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42693&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Gram Sabha shall, subject to`
  line `sub-section (2), consist of all persons whose names are included in electoral rolls referred to in section 15`
  line `within the area of the Gram Sabha:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be a member of more than one Gram Sabha.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be disqualified for being a member of the Gram Sabha, if--`
  line
  line `(a) he is not a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(c) he is for the time being disqualified from voting under the provision of any law relating to`
  line `corrupt practices and other offences in connection with election to State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42694)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Cessation of Membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42694&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member of Gram Sabha shall cease to be a member, if he has`
  line `ceased to be ordinarily resident within the Gram Sabha area.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person ceases to be a member of Gram Sabha under sub-section (1) he shall also cease`
  line `to hold any office to which he may have been elected or appointed by virtue of being a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42695)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Periodicity of Meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42695&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Gram Sabha shall meet from time to time but six months shall not`
  line `intervene between any two meetings.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42696)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Convening of Meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42696&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The meeting of the Gram Sabha shall be held in accordance with such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42697)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Quorum.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42697&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum for a meeting of the Gram Sabha shall be one-tenth of its total`
  line membership.
  line
  line `(2) If at the time appointed for the meeting, a quorum is not present, the person presiding shall wait`
  line `for thirty minutes, and if within such period, there is no quorum, the person presiding shall adjourn the`
  line `meeting to the same time on the same day in the following week. He shall similarly, after waiting for`
  line `thirty minutes, adjourn the meeting if at any time after it has begun, attention is drawn to the want of a`
  line `quorum. A notice of the meeting so fixed shall be posted in the office of the Gram Panchayat. The`
  line `business which could not be considered at the meeting so postponed for want of quorum, shall be brought`
  line `before and disposed of at the meeting so fixed or at any subsequent adjourned meeting at which there is a`
  line quorum
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42698)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Gram Sabha Meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42698&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every meeting of the Gram Sabha shall be presided over by the Pradhan`
  line `of the concerned Gram Panchayat and in his absence, by the Up-Pradhan, and in the absence of both by a`
  line `member of the Gram Panchayat to be chosen from amongst the members of the Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42699)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Agenda.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42699&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Gram Panchayat shall prepare the agenda for discussion of the Gram Sabha, such`
  line `matters shall relate to the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the annual statement of accounts of the Gram Panchayat, the report of administration of the`
  line `preceding financial year and the last audit note and replies if any, made thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) the budget of the Gram Panchayat for the next financial year; and`
  line
  line `(c) the report in respect of development programmes of the Gram Panchayat relating to the`
  line `preceding year and development programmes proposed to be undertaken during the current year.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42700)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Resolution.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42700&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any resolution relating to the functions entrusted to the Gram Sabha under`
  line `section 11, shall have to be passed by a majority of votes of the members present and voting in the`
  line `meeting of the Gram Sabha`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42701)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions of Gram Sabha.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42701&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `A Gram Sabha shall exercise the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) rendering assistance in the implementation of development schemes pertaining to the village;`
  line
  line `(b) identification of beneficiaries for the implementation of development schemes pertaining to`
  line `the village:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the Gram Sabha fails to identify the beneficiaries within a reasonable time`
  line `the Gram Panchayat can identify the beneficiaries;`
  line
  line `(c) mobilising voluntary labour and contributions in kind or cash or both for the community`
  line `welfare programmes;`
  line
  line `(d) to promote adult education and family welfare within the village;`
  line
  line `(e) promotion of unity and harmony among all sections of society in the village;`
  line
  line `(f) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42702)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vigilance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42702&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Gram Sabha may also form one or more Vigilance Committees`
  line `consisting of persons, who are not members of the Gram Panchayat to supervise the Gram Panchayat`
  line `works, schemes and other activities and to put up reports concerning them in its meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (42703)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Constitution of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42703&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Gram Panchayat for every`
  line `Gram Sabha.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Panchayat constituted under sub-section (1) shall be notified in the Official Gazette and`
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted from the date of its first meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person shall be entitled to be included in the list of electors of Gram Panchayat if he is not`
  line `less than eighteen years of age on the date of its publication under sub-section (1) and is ordinarily`
  line `resident within the area of the Gram Panchayat:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be entitled to be included in the list of the electors of any Gram`
  line `Panchayat for more than one Gram Panchayat and no person shall be entitled to be included in the`
  line `electoral roll of any Gram Panchayat for more than once:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the applicant is included in the electoral roll of any other Gram Panchayat, the`
  line `officer who includes his name shall inform the officer publishing the electoral roll of that other Gram`
  line `Panchayat and that the other officer shall, on receipt of the information, strike off the applicant's name`
  line `from that list.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression "ordinarily resident" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as has been given in section 20 of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950).`
  line
  line `(4) The name of any person included in the list of electors who becomes disqualified at any time after`
  line `his name was entered in the list, shall forthwith be struck-off from the list in which it is included:`
  line
  line `Provided that the name of any person struck-off from the electoral roll by reason of disqualification`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 3 shall forthwith be re-instated if such person ceases to`
  line `become disqualified.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal shall be made within such time and in such manner and to such authority as may be`
  line `prescribed against any order passed under sub-sections (2) and (4).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (42704)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Incorporation of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42704&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every Gram Panchayat shall, by the name notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette under section 13, be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal`
  line `with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to enter into contracts, and shall, by the said`
  line `name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (42705)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Electoral Roll of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42705&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The electoral roll of the Manipur Assembly prepared under`
  line `the provision of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) and as in force on such date as`
  line `the State Government may, by general or special order, notify in this behalf for such part of the`
  line `constituency of the Assembly as is included in the Gram Sabha, shall be the list of electors for such Gram`
  line Panchayat.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (42706)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Publication of Electoral Roll of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42706&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The list of electors referred to in`
  line `section 15 shall be published in such manner and by such authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person whose name is not included in the list of electors published under sub-section (1) may`
  line `apply within ten days from its publication to the officer publishing the same for inclusion of his name`
  line `therein and officer concerned shall, if he is satisfied that the applicant fulfils the condition mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (3) and is not disqualified from being included in the list of electors under section 15 after`
  line `making such inquiry as may be prescribed, direct his name to be included in the list of electors.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (42707)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Composition of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42707&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `A Gram Panchayat shall consist of the Pradhan and such`
  line `number of directly elected members as may be notified from time to time by the State Government and`
  line `one member for every 350 population or part thereof of the Panchayat area shall be elected as a member`
  line `of such Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (42708)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Division of Gram Sabha into territorial constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42708&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Deputy Commissioner shall,`
  line `for the conduct of the election,--`
  line
  line `(i) divide the area of the Gram Sabha into territorial constituencies in such manner that the ratio`
  line `between the population of each constituency and the number of seats allotted to it shall, as far as`
  line `practicable, be the same throughout the Gram Sabha area;`
  line
  line `(ii) determine the number of seats allotted to each constituency.`
  line
  line `(2) One member from each territorial constituency shall be elected by direct election to the Gram`
  line Panchayat.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (42709)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Reservation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42709&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Seats shall be reserved for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes in`
  line `every Gram Panchayat, and the number of seats so reserved shall bear, as nearly as may be, the same`
  line `proportion to the total number of seats to be filled by direct election in that Panchayat as the population of`
  line `Scheduled Castes or of the Scheduled Tribes in that Panchayat area bears to the total population of that`
  line `area and such seats shall be allotted by rotation to different constituencies in such Gram Panchayat, in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than one-third of the total number of seats reserved under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `reserved for women belonging to Scheduled Castes, or as the case may be, the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(3) Not less than one-third (including the number of seats reserved for women belonging to the`
  line `Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes) of the total number of seats to be filled by direct election in`
  line `every Gram Panchayat shall be reserved for women and such seats may be allotted by rotation to different`
  line `constituencies in a Gram Panchayat in such manner as may be prescribed`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (42710)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Term of the Gram Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42710&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Gram Panchayat shall continue for a term of five`
  line `years from the date appointed for its first meeting and no longer:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Gram Panchayat which is functioning immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall continue till the expiration of its duration.`
  line
  line `(2) The election to constitute a Gram Panchayat shall be completed--`
  line
  line `(a) before the expiration of its duration specified in sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of dissolution, before the expiration of a period of six months from the date of`
  line `dissolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the remainder of the period for which the dissolved Gram Panchayat would`
  line `have continued is less than six months, it shall not be necessary to hold any election under this clause`
  line `for constituting the Gram Panchayat for such period.`
  line
  line `(3) A Gram Panchayat constituted upon the dissolution of a Gram Panchayat before the expiration of`
  line `its duration, shall continue only for the remainder of the period for which the dissolved Gram Panchayat`
  line `would have continued under sub-section (1) had it not been so dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (42711)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Election of the Pradhan and members of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42711&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Pradhan and members of the`
  line `Gram Panchayat shall be elected by direct election under secret ballot by the members of the Gram Sabha`
  line `from amongst themselves in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (42800)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appointment of an Administrative Committee or Administrator on failure to elect members of Gram Panchayats and in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42800&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) If the Deputy Commissioner is satisfied that a Gram`
  line `Panchayat for a village or group of villages immediately after the establishment of such Gram Panchayat`
  line `cannot be constituted by reason of--`
  line
  line `(i) any difficulty in holding an election of the members of the Gram Panchayat; or`
  line
  line `(ii) failure to elect such members at two successive elections held under section 17; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other sufficient reason whatsoever; or`
  line
  line `(b) If at any general election to a Gram Panchayat, no member is elected or less than two-third of the`
  line `total number of members are elected, the Deputy Commissioner shall, by notification either,--`
  line
  line `(i) appoint an Administrative Committee consisting of persons qualified to be elected, the number`
  line `of such persons being equal to the number of members determined under section 17; or`
  line
  line `(ii) appoint an Administrator.`
  line
  line `(2) The members of the Administrative Committee or the Administrator shall hold office for such`
  line `period not exceeding six months as the Deputy Commissioner may specify in the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) On the appointment of an Administrative Committee or an Administrator under sub-section (1),`
  line `the persons, if any, chosen as members of the Gram Panchayat before such appointment shall cease to be`
  line `members of the Gram Panchayat and all the powers and duties of the Gram Panchayat shall be exercised`
  line `and performed by such Administrative Committee or Administrator, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The Administrative Committee or Administrator shall be deemed to be a duly constituted Gram`
  line `Panchayat for the purpose of this Act, notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions:`
  line
  line `Provided that if at any time after the appointment of the Administrative Committee or the`
  line `Administrator under sub-section (1), the Deputy Commissioner is satisfied that there is no difficulty in`
  line `duly constituting the Gram Panchayat by election of members, the Deputy Commissioner, may,`
  line `notwithstanding that the term of office for which the members of the Administrative Committee or the`
  line `Administrator had been appointed has not expired, direct by notification that the members of the`
  line `Administrative Committee or the Administrator, as the case may be, shall cease to hold office with effect`
  line `from such date as may be specified in such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (42713)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Filling of casual vacancy in the office of Pradhan and of the member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42713&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of`
  line `occurrence of any vacancy by reason of death, resignation, removal or otherwise in the office of Pradhan`
  line `or of a member of a Gram Panchayat, the vacancy shall be filled by election in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Pradhan and every Member elected to fill a casual vacancy, shall hold office for the`
  line `remaining term of office of the person in whose place he is so elected:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election for filling the casual vacancy shall be held if the vacancy is for a period of`
  line `less than six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (42714)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Election of Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42714&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Gram Panchayat shall, as soon as may be, elect one of its`
  line `members to be Up-Pradhan.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of occurrence of any vacancy by reason of death, resignation, removal or otherwise in`
  line `the office of Up-Pradhan, the Gram Panchayat shall elect another member to be the Up-Pradhan:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election shall be held if the vacancy is for a period of less than six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (42715)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Reservation of seats for Pradhan and Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42715&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the general or special order of`
  line `the Government, the Deputy Commissioner shall reserve--`
  line
  line `(i) such number of offices of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan of Gram Panchayat in the district for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes as nearly as may be, in the same proportion as the total`
  line `number of offices in the district bears to the population of the Scheduled Castes or of the Scheduled`
  line `Tribes in the district bears to the total population of that district;`
  line
  line `(ii) not less than one-third of the total number of offices of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan, as the case`
  line `may be, of the Gram Panchayat in the district shall be reserved for women:`
  line
  line `Provided that the offices reserved under this section shall be allotted by rotation to different Gram`
  line `Panchayats in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (42716)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure for election of Up-Pradhan on the establishment of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42716&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `On the`
  line `establishment of Gram Panchayat for the first time under this Act, or on its reconstitution or establishment`
  line `under section 20, a meeting of the Gram Panchayat shall be called immediately by the prescribed officer`
  line `who shall himself preside over the meeting, but shall have no right to vote, and in such meeting, the`
  line `Up-Pradhan shall be elected.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (42717)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Term of the office of the Pradhan and Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42717&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of every Pradhan`
  line `and Up-Pradhan of the Gram Panchayat shall, save as otherwise provided in this Act, cease on the expiry`
  line `of the term of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) Pradhan and Up-Pradhan shall be entitled to such honoraria and other allowances, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Every member of the Gram Panchayat shall be entitled to receive such honoraria and allowances`
  line `as may be fixed by the Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (42718)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Powers, functions and duties of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42718&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Pradhan shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be responsible for convening the meeting of Gram Sabha and preside over its meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) be responsible for convening the meeting of Gram Panchayat and shall preside over its`
  line meetings;
  line
  line `(c) be responsible for the maintenance of the records of the Gram Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(d) have the general responsibility for the financial and executive administration of the Gram`
  line Panchayat;
  line
  line `(e) exercise administrative supervision and control over the work of the staff of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat and the officers and employees whose services may be placed at the disposal of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat by any other authority;`
  line
  line `(f) for the transaction of business connected with this Act, or for the purpose of making any order`
  line `authorised thereby, exercise such powers, perform such functions and discharge such duties as may`
  line `be exercised, performed or discharged by the Gram Panchayat under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Pradhan shall not exercise such powers, perform such functions or discharge`
  line `such duties as may be required by the rules made under this Act to be exercised, performed or`
  line `discharged by the Gram Panchayat at a meeting; and`
  line
  line `(g) exercise such other powers, perform such other functions and discharge such other duties as`
  line `the Gram Panchayat may, by general or special resolution direct or as the Government may by rules`
  line `made in this behalf, prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) The Up-Pradhan shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise such of the powers, perform such of the functions and discharge such of the duties of`
  line `Pradhan as the Pradhan may from time to time, subject to rules made in this behalf by the`
  line `Government, delegate to him by order in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Pradhan may at any time withdraw all or any of the powers, functions and`
  line `duties so delegated to the Up-Pradhan;`
  line
  line `(b) during the absence of the Pradhan, exercise all the powers, perform all the functions and`
  line `discharge all the duties of the Pradhan;`
  line
  line `(c) exercise such other powers, perform such other functions and discharge such other duties as`
  line `the Gram Panchayat may, by general or special resolution, direct or as the Government may, by rules`
  line `made in this behalf, prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (42719)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Resignation of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42719&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Pradhan and the Up-Pradhan, as the case`
  line `may be, may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the prescribed authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every resignation under sub-section (1) shall take effect on the expiry of fifteen days from the`
  line `date of its receipt by the prescribed authority, unless within this period of fifteen days he withdraws such`
  line `resignation by writing under his hand addressed to the prescribed authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Up-Pradhan shall vacate the office if he ceases to be a member of a Gram Panchayat`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (42720)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `No confidence motion against the Pradhan and Up-Pradhan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42720&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Pradhan and every`
  line `Up-Pradhan shall be deemed to have vacated his office forthwith if a resolution expressing want of`
  line `confidence in him is passed by a majority of not less than two-third of the members of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat present and voting, at a meeting specially convened for the purpose. The requisition for such a`
  line `special meeting shall be signed by not less than half of the total number of members of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat and shall be delivered to the prescribed authority. The prescribed authority shall within seven`
  line `days from the date of the receipt of the requisition, convene a special meeting of the Gram Panchayat. The`
  line `meeting shall be held on a day not later than fifteen days from the date of issue of the notice of the`
  line `meeting. The meeting shall be presided over by the prescribed authority. In the initial two years of their`
  line `term as Pradhan and Up-Pradhan of a Gram Panchayat on such motion of no confidence shall be moved`
  line `against them. If the motion of no confidence is once rejected, no fresh motion of no confidence shall be`
  line `brought before the Gram Panchayat within a period of one year from the date of such rejection of the`
  line motion.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions under this Act, a Pradhan and Up-Pradhan may be removed`
  line `from office by the Government for misconduct in the discharge of his duties or neglect or, incapacity to`
  line `perform his duties or for being persistently remiss in the discharge thereof, or guilty of any disgraceful`
  line `conduct:`
  line
  line `Provided that, no such Pradhan, or Up-Pradhan be removed from office unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to defend himself.`
  line
  line `(3) The Pradhan or Up-Pradhan removed under sub-section (2) shall not be eligible for re-election as`
  line `Pradhan or Up-Pradhan during the remaining term of office.`
  line
  line `(4) A Pradhan or Up-Pradhan removed from his office under sub-section (2) shall cease to be a`
  line `member of the Gram Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (42721)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Resignation of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42721&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `A member of a Gram Panchayat may resign his membership in`
  line `writing under his hand addressed to the Pradhan of the Gram Panchayat and his seat shall become vacant`
  line `on the expiry of fifteen clear days from the date of such resignation unless within the said period of`
  line `fifteen days, he withdraws such resignation by writing under his hand addressed to the Pradhan.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (42722)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Meeting of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42722&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Gram Panchayat shall meet for the transaction of business`
  line `at least once in two months at the office of the Gram Panchayat and at such time as the Pradhan may`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(2) The Pradhan may, whenever he thinks fit, and shall, upon the written request of not less than`
  line `one-third of the total number of members and on a date within fifteen days from the receipt of such`
  line `request, call a special meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Seven clear days' notice of an ordinary meeting and three clear days notice of a special meeting`
  line `specifying the place, date and time of such meeting and business to be transacted thereat, shall be given`
  line `by the Secretary to the members and such officers as the Government may prescribe, and affixed on the`
  line `notice board of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(4) The officers to whom notice is given under sub-section (3) and other Government officers having`
  line `jurisdiction over the Gram Panchayat area or any part thereof shall be entitled to attend every meeting of`
  line `Gram Panchayat and take part in the proceedings but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Pradhan fails to call a special meeting as provided in sub-section (2), the Up-Pradhan or, in`
  line `his absence, one-third of the total number of members may call such a meeting for a day not more than`
  line `fifteen days thereafter and require the Secretary to give notice to the members and to take such action as`
  line `may be necessary to convene the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (42723)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Minutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42723&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes shall be kept of the names of the members and of the officers, if any,`
  line `present, and of the proceedings at each meeting of the Gram Panchayat and if any member present at the`
  line `meeting so desires, of the names of the member voting respectively for or against any resolution, in a`
  line `book to be provided for the purpose and after they are read over and agreed to, shall be signed by the`
  line `Pradhan and Up-Pradhan or person presiding at such meeting, and shall at all reasonable times be open to`
  line `inspection by any member of the Gram Panchayat. Any person may inspect the copy of minutes of the`
  line `meeting. The minutes books shall always be kept in the office of the Gram Panchayat and shall be in the`
  line `custody of the Secretary of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every resolution passed by the Gram Panchayat shall within ten days from the date of`
  line `meeting, be forwarded by the Secretary to the Chief Executive Officer`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (42724)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Quorum and procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42724&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum for a meeting of the Gram Panchayat shall be onehalf of the total number of members. If, at the time appointed for the meeting, a quorum is not present, the`
  line `presiding authority shall wait for thirty minutes, and if within such period there is no quorum, the`
  line `presiding authority shall adjourn the meeting to such time on the following day or such future day as he`
  line `may fix. He shall, similarly, after waiting for thirty minutes adjourn the meeting if, at any time, after it has`
  line `begun, attention is drawn to the want of a quorum. A notice of the meeting so fixed shall be pasted in the`
  line `office of the Gram Panchayat. The business which could not be considered at the meeting so postponed`
  line `for want of quorum, shall be brought before and disposed of at the meeting so fixed or at any subsequent`
  line `adjourned meeting at which there is a quorum.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided by or under this Act, at every meeting of Gram Panchayat, the`
  line `Pradhan or in his absence the Up-Pradhan shall preside, and in the absence of both, the members present`
  line `shall elect one from amongst themselves to preside for the occasion.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions shall, unless otherwise specifically provided, be decided by a majority of votes of`
  line `the members present and voting. The Pradhan or Up-Pradhan or person presiding, as the case may be,`
  line `unless he refrains from voting shall give his vote before declaring the number of votes for and against a`
  line `question and in the case of equality of votes, he may give his casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) No member of a Gram Panchayat shall vote on, or take part in the discussion of, any question`
  line `coming up for consideration at a meeting of a Gram Panchayat, if the question is one in which, apart from`
  line `its general application to the public, he has any pecuniary interest, and if the person presiding has such an`
  line `interest, he shall not preside over the meeting when such question comes up for consideration.`
  line
  line `(5) If the person presiding is believed by any member present at the meeting to have any such`
  line `pecuniary interest in any matter under discussion, and if a motion to that effect be carried, he shall not`
  line `preside at the meeting during such discussion or vote on or take part in it. Any member of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat may be chosen to preside at the meeting during the continuance of such discussion.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (42725)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Functions of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42725&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such conditions as may be specified by the`
  line `Government from time to time, the Gram Panchayat shall perform the functions specified below:--`
  line
  line `(1) General Functions:--`
  line
  line `(a) preparation of annual plans for the development of the Panchayat area;`
  line
  line `(b) preparation of annual budget;`
  line
  line `(c) power for mobilising reliefs in natural calamities;`
  line
  line `(d) removal of encroachments on public properties;`
  line
  line `(e) organising voluntary labour and contribution for community works; and`
  line
  line `(f) maintenance of essential statistics of village(s).`
  line
  line `(2) Agriculture, including Agriculture Extension:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion and development of agriculture and horticulture;`
  line
  line `(b) development of waste lands;`
  line
  line `(c) development and maintenance of grazing lands and preventing their unauthorised`
  line alienation;
  line
  line `(d) promote land improvement and soil conservation measures; and`
  line
  line `(e) promote measures for implementation of land reforms and land consolidation.`
  line
  line `(3) Animal husbandry, Dairying and Poultry:--`
  line
  line `(a) improvement of breed of cattle, poultry and other live-stock;`
  line
  line `(b) promotion of dairy farming, poultry and piggery; and`
  line
  line `(c) grassland development.`
  line
  line `(4) Fisheries:--`
  line
  line `development of fisheries in the village(s)`
  line
  line `(5) Social and Farm Forestry, Minor Forest produce Fuel and Fodder:--`
  line
  line `(a) planting and preservation of trees on the sides of roads and other public lands under its`
  line control;
  line
  line `(b) fuel plantations and fodder development;`
  line
  line `(c) promotion of farm forestry; and`
  line
  line `(d) development of social forestry.`
  line
  line `(6) Khadi, Village and Cottage Industries:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of rural and cottage industries;`
  line
  line `(b) organisation of awareness camps, seminars and training programmes, agricultural and`
  line `industrial exhibitions for the benefit of the rural areas; and`
  line
  line `(c) identification of traditional skills in the area to develop small scale industries and`
  line `popularising food processing units.`
  line
  line `(7) Rural Housing:--`
  line
  line `(a) implementation of house building programme; and`
  line
  line `(b) maintenance of records relating to the houses, sites and other private and public`
  line properties.
  line
  line `(8) Drinking water:--`
  line
  line `(a) construction, repair and maintenance of drinking water wells, tanks and ponds;`
  line
  line `(b) prevention and control of water pollution; and`
  line
  line `(c) maintenance of rural water supply schemes.`
  line
  line `(9) Roads, buildings, culverts, bridges, ferries, waterways and other means of communication:--`
  line
  line `(a) construction and maintenance of village roads, drains and culverts;`
  line
  line `(b) maintenance of buildings under its control or transferred to it by the Government or any`
  line `public authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) maintenance of boats, ferries and waterways.`
  line
  line `(10) Non-Conventional Energy Source:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion and development of non-conventional, energy schemes;`
  line
  line `(b) maintenance of community, non-conventional, energy devices, including bio-gas plants;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) propagation of improved chulhas and other efficient energy devices.`
  line
  line `(11) Poverty Alleviation Programme:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of public awareness and participation in poverty alleviation programmes for`
  line `fuller employment and creation of productive assets;`
  line
  line `(b) selection of beneficiaries under various programmes through Gram Sabha; and`
  line
  line `(c) participation in effective implementation and monitoring.`
  line
  line `(12) Education including primary schools and secondary schools:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of public awareness and participation in primary and secondary education with`
  line `special emphasis on technical training and vocational education; and`
  line
  line `(b) ensuring full enrolment and attendance in primary and secondary schools and its`
  line management.
  line
  line `(13) Adult and non-formal Education:--`
  line
  line `promotion of Adult literacy.`
  line
  line `(14) Libraries:--`
  line
  line `village libraries and reading rooms.`
  line
  line `(15) Cultural activities:--`
  line
  line `promotion of social and cultural activities.`
  line
  line `(16) Markets and fairs:--`
  line
  line `regulation of fairs (including cattle fairs) and festivals.`
  line
  line `(17) Rural sanitation:--`
  line
  line `(a) maintenance of general sanitation;`
  line
  line `(b) cleaning of public roads, drains, tanks, wells and other public places;`
  line
  line `(c) maintenance and regulation of burning and burial grounds;`
  line
  line `(d) construction and maintenance of public latrines; and`
  line
  line `(e) management and control of washing and bathing ghats.`
  line
  line `(18) Public health and family welfare:--`
  line
  line `(a) implementation of family welfare programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) prevention and remedial measures against epidemics;`
  line
  line `(c) regulation of sale of meat, fish and other perishable food articles;`
  line
  line `(d) participation in programmes of human and animal vaccination;`
  line
  line `(e) regulation of eating and entertainment establishments;`
  line
  line `(f) destruction of stray dogs;`
  line
  line `(g) regulation of curing, tanning and dyeing of skins and hides; and`
  line
  line `(h) regulation of offensive and dangerous trades.`
  line
  line `(19) Woman and child development:--`
  line
  line `(a) participation in the implementation of woman and child welfare programmes; and`
  line
  line `(b) promotion of school health and nutrition programmes.`
  line
  line `(20) Social welfare including welfare of the handicapped and mentally retarded:--`
  line
  line `(a) participation in the implementation of the social programmes, including welfare of the`
  line `handicapped, mentally retarded and destitute; and`
  line
  line `(b) monitoring of the old-age and widows pension schemes;`
  line
  line `(21) Welfare of the weaker section and in particular the Scheduled Castes and Scheduled`
  line `Tribes:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of public awareness with regard to welfare of Scheduled Castes, Scheduled`
  line `Tribes and other Weaker Sections; and`
  line
  line `(b) participation in the implementation of the specific programmes for the welfare of the`
  line `weaker sections.`
  line
  line `(22) Public distribution system:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of the public awareness with regard to the distribution of essential`
  line `commodities; and`
  line
  line `(b) monitoring the public distribution system.`
  line
  line `(23) Maintenance of community assets:--`
  line
  line `(a) maintenance of community assets; and`
  line
  line `(b) preservation and maintenance of other community assets.`
  line
  line `(24) Construction and maintenance of Dharmashalas, Chatras and similar institutions.`
  line
  line `(25) Construction and maintenance of cattle sheds, pounds and cart stands.`
  line
  line `(26) Construction and maintenance of slaughter houses.`
  line
  line `(27) Maintenance of public parks, playgrounds.`
  line
  line `(28) Regulation of manure pits in public places.`
  line
  line `(29) Establishment and control of shandies.`
  line
  line `(30) Irrigation, water management and watershed development:--`
  line
  line `(a) promote measures for construction and maintenance of minor irrigation works and`
  line `watershed development programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) develop ground water resources;`
  line
  line `(c) providing for timely and equitable distribution of irrigation water.`
  line
  line `(31) Rural electrification including distribution of electricity:--`
  line
  line `(a) promote extension of electricity to unelectrified areas;`
  line
  line `(b) help in prevention of illegal tapping of electricity; and`
  line
  line `(c) help in the recovery and collection of electricity due.`
  line
  line `(32) Such other functions as may be entrusted.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (42726)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Assignment of functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42726&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, by notification and subject to such conditions`
  line `as may be specified therein--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer to any Gram Panchayat the management and maintenance of a forest situated in the`
  line `panchayat area;`
  line
  line `(b) make over to the Gram Panchayat the management of waste lands, pasture lands or vacant`
  line `lands belonging to the Government situated within the panchayat area;`
  line
  line `(c) entrust the Gram Panchayat with the collection of land revenue on behalf of the Government`
  line `and the maintenance of such records as are connected therewith; and`
  line
  line `(d) entrust such other functions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no entrustment under clause (c) shall be made without the concurrence of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when any transfer of the management and maintenance of a forest is made under`
  line `clause (a) the Government shall direct that any amount required for such management and maintenance or`
  line `an adequate portion of the income from such forest be placed at the disposal of the Gram Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (42727)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `General powers of the Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42727&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `A Gram Panchayat shall have powers to do all acts`
  line `necessary for or incidental to the carrying out the functions entrusted assigned or delegated to it and, in`
  line `particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing powers, to exercise all powers specified under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (42728)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Standing Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42728&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Gram Panchayat shall constitute the following committees by`
  line election--
  line
  line `(i) Production Committee for performing functions relating to agricultural productions, animal`
  line `husbandry and rural industries and poverty alleviation programmes;`
  line
  line `(ii) Social Justice Committee for performing functions relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of education, economic, social, cultural and other interests of the Scheduled`
  line `Castes and Scheduled Tribes and Backward Classes;`
  line
  line `(b) protection of such castes and classes from social injustice and any form of exploitation;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) welfare of women and children.`
  line
  line `(iii) Amenities Committee to perform functions in respect of education, public health, public`
  line `works and other functions of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) Each Committee shall consist of not less than three and not more than five members including`
  line `the Pradhan and Up-Pradhan as the case may be. The Pradhan shall be the ex officio member and`
  line `Chairman of Production Committee and Amenities Committee. The Pradhan shall be the ex officio member and Chairman of the Social Justice Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Social Justice Committee shall consist of at least one member who is a woman and`
  line `one member belonging to the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(b) Each Committee shall be competent to co-opt in such manner as may be prescribed, members of`
  line `farmers' club, mahila mandals, yuvak mandals and other similar bodies recognised by the Government. A`
  line `representative of Co-operative societies in the panchayat areas shall be co-opted to the Production`
  line `Committee. The rights and liabilities of the co-opted members shall be such, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Standing Committee shall perform the functions referred to above, to the extent the powers`
  line `are delegated to them by the Gram Panchayat`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (42729)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Property and funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42729&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every Gram Panchayat there shall be constituted a Gram`
  line `Panchayat Fund bearing the name of the Gram Panchayat and there shall be placed to the credit thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) contributions and grants, if any, made by the Central or State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) contributions and grants, if any, made by the Zilla Parishad or any other local authority;`
  line
  line `(c) loans, if any, granted by the Central or the State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) all receipts on accounts of taxes, rates and fees levied by it; and`
  line
  line `(e) all other sums received by or on behalf of other Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Gram Panchayat shall set apart and apply annually such sum as may be required to meet--`
  line
  line `(a) The cost of its own administration including the payment of salary, allowances, provident`
  line `fund and gratuity to the officers and employees and to the Secretary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total expenditure on establishment shall not exceed one-third of the total`
  line `expenditure, of the Gram Panchayat in any year.`
  line
  line `(b) Every Gram Panchayat shall have the power to spend such sums as it thinks fit for carrying`
  line `out the purpose of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) The Gram Panchayat Fund shall be vested in the Gram Panchayat and the balance to the credit`
  line `of the Fund shall be kept in such custody as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (42730)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Taxation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42730&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, a Gram Panchayat shall`
  line `impose yearly tax on lands and buildings within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such maximum rates as the Government may prescribe, a Gram Panchayat may levy the`
  line `following fees and rates, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a fee for providing sanitary arrangements at such places of worship or pilgrimage, fairs and`
  line `melas within its jurisdiction as may be specified by the Government by notification;`
  line
  line `(b) a lighting rate, where arrangement for lighting of public streets and places is made by the`
  line `Gram Panchayat within its jurisdiction; and`
  line
  line `(c) a conservancy rate, where arrangement for clearing private latrines, urinals and cesspools is`
  line `made by the Gram Panchayat within its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (42731)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Financial assistance to Gram Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42731&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this section, every`
  line `Gram Panchayat shall, after a re-appropriation made by law in this behalf, be entitled to receive`
  line `grants-in-aid from the Consolidated Fund of the State as recommended by the State Finance Commission,`
  line `constituted under section 97 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (42732)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Budget of the Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42732&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Gram Panchayat shall, at such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, prepare during each year a budget of its estimated receipts and`
  line `disbursements for the following year and shall submit the budget to the Zilla Parishad having jurisdiction`
  line `over the area of the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) The Zilla Parishad may, within such time as may be prescribed, either approve the budget or`
  line `return it to the Gram Panchayat for such modifications as it may direct. On such modifications being`
  line
  line `made the budget shall be resubmitted within such time as may be prescribed for approval of the Zilla`
  line Parishad.
  line
  line `(3) No expenditure shall be incurred unless the budget is approved by the Zilla Parishad. If the Zilla`
  line `Parishad does not convey its approval within the time prescribed for the purpose, the budget will be`
  line `deemed to have been approved by the Zilla Parishad`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (42733)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title Accounts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42733&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Accounts of the income and expenditure of every Gram Panchayat shall be kept in`
  line `such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (42734)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42734&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of a Gram Panchayat shall be audited by the Director, Local Fund`
  line `Audit and Accounts of the Government of Manipur in such manner as may be prescribed and a copy of`
  line `the audit report shall be forwarded to the Gram Panchayat within one month of the completion of the`
  line audit.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the audit report referred to in sub-section (1), the Gram Panchayat shall either`
  line `remedy the defects or irregularities which have been pointed out in the audit report and send to the Zilla`
  line `Parishad within three months an intimation of its having done so, or shall, within the said period, supply`
  line `any further explanation to the prescribed authority in regard to such defects or irregularities as it is`
  line `required to furnish`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (42735)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Staff of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42735&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Secretary for every Gram Panchayat who shall`
  line `be appointed in such manner as may be prescribed and shall draw his salary and allowances from the`
  line `Gram Panchayat Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary shall be in charge of the office of the Gram Panchayat and shall perform all the`
  line `duties and exercise all the powers imposed or conferred upon him by or under this Act or any rules or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government shall make rules relating to the method of recruitment and the terms and`
  line `conditions of service including the pay and allowances, superannuation, provident fund and gratuity of the`
  line Secretary.
  line
  line `(4) Subject to rules as may be prescribed by Government regarding discipline and control, the`
  line `Secretary shall act in all matters under the control of Gram Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (42736)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Staffing pattern and category of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42736&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by order, specify the`
  line `staffing pattern, the scales of pay and mode of recruitment of staff of Gram Panchayats.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Panchayat shall, subject to sub-section (1), determine and submit for approval of the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer a category of employees specifying the designation and grades and the salaries`
  line `and allowances payable to its officers other than the Secretary required for carrying out the duties`
  line `imposed upon the Gram Panchayat by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (42737)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Appointment and control of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42737&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sections 45 and 46 the`
  line `Gram Panchayat may, with the prior approval of the Chief Executive Officer appoint other employees of`
  line `the Gram Panchayat and pay their salaries from the Gram Panchayat fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that in making appointments, posts for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and`
  line `other socially and educationally backward classes of citizens shall be reserved in the same manner and to`
  line `the same extent as is applicable for the recruitment to posts in the State Civil Services.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (42738)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Establishment of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42738&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette establish a Zilla Parishad for a district and having jurisdiction over it, with effect from such date`
  line `as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Zilla Parishad shall be a corporate body by the name of its district, having perpetual`
  line `succession and common seal and subject to such restrictions as are imposed by or under this or any, other`
  line `enactment, shall be vested with the capacity of sueing or being sued in its corporate name, of acquiring,`
  line `holding and transferring property movable or immovable, whether without or within the limits of the area`
  line `over which it has authority, of entering into contracts and of doing all things, necessary, proper or`
  line `expedient for the purpose for which it is constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (42739)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Composition of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42739&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Zilla Parishad shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the members directly elected from the territorial constituencies in the district under section 50;`
  line
  line `(b) the members of the House of the People and the members of the State Legislative Assembly`
  line `representing a part or whole of the district whose constituencies lie within the district; and`
  line
  line `(c) ten per cent. of the Pradhans of the Gram Panchayats in the district:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the total number of members under clauses (b) and (c) exceed the total number of`
  line `members under clause (a), only one-third of the members under clause (c) shall be selected on rotation for`
  line `a period of one year by lot as the Government may decide from time to time and district to district,`
  line `subject to the condition that a Pradhan who was a member under this clause for one year shall not be`
  line `eligible to become member for a second term during the remainder of his term of office as Pradhan:`
  line
  line `Provided further that all members of the Zilla Parishad whether elected or not from territorial`
  line `constituencies in the Zilla Parishad area shall have the right to vote in the meeting of the Zilla Parishad`
  line `except in the election of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (42740)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Elected Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42740&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, determine`
  line `the number of directly elected members from territorial constituencies keeping in view the overall`
  line `population of the district at a rate of the one member for every 15,000 population or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) For the conduct of the election, the prescribed authority shall, in accordance with such rules as`
  line `may be prescribed in this behalf by the Government,--`
  line
  line `(a) divide the area of Zilla Parishad into territorial constituencies in such manner so that the ratio`
  line `between the population of each constituency and the numbers of seats allotted to it shall, so far as`
  line `may be practicable, be the same throughout the panchayat area and determine the number of seats`
  line `allotted to each constituency;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to each territorial constituency shall elect one or more members through direct`
  line `election in the manner prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (42741)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Filling of casual vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42741&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `If vacancy of a member in Zilla Parishad occurs because of`
  line `resignation, death, removal or otherwise, it shall be filled by election in the prescribed manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election for filling the casual vacancy shall be held if the vacancy is for a period of`
  line `less than six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (42742)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title Reservation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42742&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Seats shall be reserved for--`
  line
  line `(a) the Scheduled Castes;`
  line
  line `(b) the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `in every Zilla Parishad and the number of seats shall bear, as nearly as may be, the same proportion to the`
  line `total number of seats to be filled by direct election in that Zilla Parishad as the population of the`
  line `Scheduled Castes in that Zilla Parishad area or of the Scheduled Tribes in that Zilla Parishad area bears to`
  line `the total population of that area and such seats may be allotted by rotation to different constituencies in a`
  line `Zilla Parishad in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than one-third of the total number of seats reserved under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `reserved for women belonging to the Scheduled Castes or, as the case may be, the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(3) Not less than one-third (including the number of seats reserved for women belonging to Scheduled`
  line `Castes and Scheduled Tribes) of the total number of seats filled by direct election in every Zilla Parishad`
  line `shall be reserved for women and such seats may be allotted by rotation to different constituencies in a`
  line `Zilla Parishad, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (42743)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Term of a Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42743&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Zilla Parishad shall continue for five years from the date`
  line `of its first meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Zilla Parishad which is functioning immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall continue till the expiration of its duration.`
  line
  line `(2) An election to constitute a Zilla Parishad shall be completed:--`
  line
  line `(a) before the expiry of its duration specified in sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of its dissolution, before the expiration of a period of six months from the date of such`
  line `dissolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the remainder of the period for which the dissolved Zilla Parishad would have`
  line `continued, is less than six months, it shall not be necessary to hold any election under this clause for such`
  line period.
  line
  line `(3) A Zilla Parishad constituted upon the dissolution of a Zilla Parishad before the expiration of its`
  line `duration shall continue only for the remainder of the period for which the dissolved Zilla Parishad would`
  line `have continued under sub-section (1) had it not been so dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (42744)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Election of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42744&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The elected members of the Zilla Parishad`
  line `referred to in section 50 shall, as soon as may be, elect two members from amongst themselves to be`
  line `respectively Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha thereof and so often as there is a casual vacancy in the Office`
  line `of the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha, they shall elect another member from amongst themselves to be`
  line `Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election shall be held if the vacancy is for period of less than one month.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government, shall in the prescribed manner reserve--`
  line
  line `(a) such number of offices of the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha of Zilla Parishad in the State for`
  line `persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes shall as nearly as may be, the same`
  line `proportion to the total number of offices in the Zilla Parishad as the population of the Scheduled`
  line `Castes or of the Scheduled Tribes in the State bear to the total population of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) not less than one-third of the total number of offices of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha in the`
  line `State from each category which are reserved for persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes and those which are unreserved, for women:`
  line
  line `Provided that the offices reserved under this section shall be allotted by rotation to different Zilla`
  line Parishads.
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha shall hold office for the`
  line `term of office of the members of the Zilla Parishad`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (42745)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Salary and allowances to the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42745&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `salary and allowances of the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every member of the Zilla Parishad other than the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha shall be entitled`
  line `to receive, such sitting fee and allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (42746)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Powers, funtions and duties of the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42746&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adhyaksha`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) perform all the duties imposed and exercise all the powers conferred on the Adhyaksha under`
  line `this Act and rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) convene, preside over, and conduct meetings of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(c) exercise administrative supervision and control over the Chief Executive Officer and through`
  line `him, all officers and other employees of the Zilla Parishad and the officers and employees whose`
  line `services may be placed at the disposal of the Zilla Parishad by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) exercise such other powers, perform such other functions and discharge such other duties as`
  line `the Zilla Parishad may, by general resolution direct or as the Government may, by rules made in this`
  line `behalf, prescribe;`
  line
  line `(e) exercise overall supervision over the financial and executive administration of the Zilla`
  line `Parishad and place before the Zilla Parishad all questions connected therewith which shall appear to`
  line `him to require its orders and for this purpose may call for records of the Zilla Parishad; and`
  line
  line `(f) have power to accord sanction up to a total sum of rupees one lakh in a year for the purpose of`
  line `providing immediate relief to those who are affected by natural calamities in the district:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Adhyaksha shall place at the next meeting of the Zilla Parishad for its ratification,`
  line `the details of such sanctions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Up-Adhyaksha shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in the absence of the Adhyaksha, preside over the meetings of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(b) exercise such powers and perform such duties of the Adhyaksha as the Adhyaksha from time`
  line `to time may, subject to the rules as may be prescribed delegate to him by order in writing; and`
  line
  line `(c) pending the election of the Adhyaksha or during the absence of the Adhyaksha from the`
  line `district, or by reason of leave for a period exceeding thirty days, exercise the powers and perform the`
  line `duties of the Adhyaksha`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (42747)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Resignation or removal of the Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42747&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adhyaksha may`
  line `resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Commissioner, and the Up-Adhyaksha may`
  line `resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Adhyaksha.`
  line
  line `(2) Every resignation under sub-section (1) shall take effect on the expiry of fifteen days from the`
  line `date of its receipt by the prescribed authority, unless within this period of fifteen days he withdraws such`
  line `resignation by writing under his hand addressed to the prescribed authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha shall vacate the office if he ceases to be a member of the`
  line `Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha shall be deemed to have vacated his office forthwith if a`
  line `resolution expressing want of confidence in him is passed by a majority of the total number of elected`
  line `members of the territorial constituencies of the Zilla Parishad at a meeting specially convened for the`
  line `purpose. The requisition for such a special meeting shall be signed by not less than one-fifth of the total`
  line `membership of the Zilla Parishad and shall be delivered to the Adhyaksha. The Adhyaksha shall, within`
  line `seven days from the date of receipt of the requisition, convene a special meeting of the Zilla Parishad. The`
  line `meeting shall be held on a day not later than fifteen days from the date of issue of the notice of the`
  line `meeting. The meeting shall be presided over by the Adhyaksha, if the motion is against the`
  line `Up-Adhyaksha and in the case of Adhyaksha, the Up-Adhyaksha shall preside over the meeting, if it is`
  line `against both, a member nominated from amongst themselves by the members present in such meeting`
  line `shall preside over such meeting. In the initial two years of their term as Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha, as`
  line `the case may be, of Zilla Parishad, no motion of no-confidence shall be brought against them.`
  line
  line `(5) If the motion of no-confidence against the Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha or both is once rejected,`
  line `no fresh motion of no-confidence against the Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha or both, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be brought before the Zilla Parishad within a period of one year from the date of such rejection of`
  line `the motion.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (42748)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Resignation of Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42748&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `A member of a Zilla Parishad may resign his membership in writing`
  line `under his hand addressed to the Adhyaksha of the Zilla Parishad and his seat shall become vacant on the`
  line `expiry of fifteen clear days from the date of such resignation, unless within the said period of fifteen days,`
  line `he withdraws such resignation by writing under his hand addressed to the Adhyaksha.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (42749)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Meeting of the Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42749&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Zilla Parishad shall hold meetings at least once in`
  line `every three months, at such time and at such place within the local limits of the district concerned as the`
  line `Zilla Parishad may fix at the immediately preceding meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first meeting of a newly constituted Zilla Parishad shall be held at such time and at`
  line `such place within the local limits of the district concerned, as the prescribed authority may fix:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Adhyaksha when required in writing by one fifth of the members of the Zilla`
  line `Parishad to call a meeting he shall do so within ten days, failing which the aforesaid members may call a`
  line `meeting after giving intimation to the prescribed authority and seven clear days notice to the Adhyaksha`
  line `and the other members of the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(2) One-third of the total number of members of the Zilla Parishad shall form a quorum for`
  line `transacting the business at the meeting of the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions coming before the Zilla Parishad shall be decided, by a majority of votes and in case`
  line `of equality of votes, the Adhyaksha or the member presiding shall have a casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) Every meeting shall be presided over by the Adhyaksha or if he is absent by the Up-Adhyaksha`
  line `and if both the Adhyaksha and the Up-Adhyaksha are absent or if the Adhyaksha is absent and there is no`
  line `Up-Adhyaksha the members present shall elect one from among themselves to preside over the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (42750)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title Minutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42750&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes shall be kept of the names of the members and of the officers, if any,`
  line `present, and of the proceedings at each meeting of the Zilla Parishad and if any member present at the`
  line `meeting so desires, of the names of the members voting respectively for or against any resolution, in a`
  line `book to be provided for purpose and after they are read over and agreed to, shall be signed by the`
  line `Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha or person presiding at such meeting, and shall at all reasonable times be`
  line `open to inspection by any member of the Zilla Parishad. Any person may inspect the copy of the minutes`
  line `of the meeting. The minutes books shall always be kept in the office of the Zilla Parishad and shall be in`
  line `the custody of the Chief Executive Officer of the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every resolution passed by the Zilla Parishad shall within ten days from the date of its`
  line `passing in the meeting, be forwarded by the Chief Executive Officer to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (42751)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Functions and powers of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42751&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any transfer of a subject to the Zilla Parishad`
  line `shall be with the approval of the Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the condition and exceptions as the Government may, from time to time, impose, it`
  line `shall be the function of the Zilla Parishad to prepare plans for economic development and social justice of`
  line `the District, and to ensure the coordinated implementation of such plans in respect of matters including`
  line `those mentioned below, namely--:`
  line
  line `1. AGRICULTURE AND AGRICULTURAL EXTENSION:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of measures to increase agricultural production and to popularise the use of`
  line `improved agricultural implements and the adoption of improved agricultural practices;`
  line
  line `(ii) establishment and maintenance of godowns;`
  line
  line `(iii) conducting agricultural fairs and exhibitions;`
  line
  line `(iv) training of farmers;`
  line
  line `(v) land improvement and soil conservation; and`
  line
  line `(vi) promotion of agricultural extension works.`
  line
  line `2. IRRIGATION GROUND WATER RESOURCES AND WATERSHED DEVELOPMENT:`
  line
  line `(i) construction, renovation and maintenance of minor irrigation works and lift irrigation;`
  line
  line `(ii) providing for the timely and equitable distribution, and full use of water under irrigation`
  line `schemes under the control of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(iii) development of ground water resources;`
  line
  line `(iv) installation of community pump sets; and`
  line
  line `(v) watershed development programme.`
  line
  line `3. HORTICULTURE:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of rural parks and gardens;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion of cultivation of fruits and vegetables; and`
  line
  line `(iii) promotion of farms.`
  line
  line `4. STATISTICS:`
  line
  line `(i) publication of statistical and other information relating to activities of Gram Panchayats`
  line `and Zilla Parishads;`
  line
  line `(ii) co-ordination and use of statistics and other information required for the activities of the`
  line `Gram Panchayats and Zilla Parishads; and`
  line
  line `(iii) periodical supervision and evaluation of project and programmes entrusted to the Gram`
  line `Panchayats and Zilla Parishads.`
  line
  line `5. DISTRIBUTION OF ESSENTIAL COMMODITIES.`
  line
  line `6. SOIL CONSERVATION AND LAND REFORMS:`
  line
  line `(i) soil conservation measures;`
  line
  line `(ii) land reclamation and land development works; and`
  line
  line `(iii) promote implementation of land reforms and land consolidation.`
  line
  line `7. MARKETING:`
  line
  line `(i) development of regulated markets and marketing yards; and`
  line
  line `(ii) grading and quality control of agriculture products.`
  line
  line `8. SOCIAL FORESTRY:`
  line
  line `(i) organise campaign for tree planting; and`
  line
  line `(ii) planting and maintenance of trees.`
  line
  line `9. ANIMAL HUSBANDRY AND DAIRYING:`
  line
  line `(i) improvement of breed of cows and pigs;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion of poultry farms, duck farms and goat farms;`
  line
  line `(iii) promotion of fodder development programmes;`
  line
  line `(iv) promotion of dairy farming, poultry and piggery; and`
  line
  line `(v) prevention of epidemics and contagious diseases.`
  line
  line `10. MINOR FOREST PRODUCE, FUEL AND FODDER:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of social and farm forestry, fuel plantation and fodder development;`
  line
  line `(ii) management of minor forest produce of the forests raised in community lands; and`
  line
  line `(iii) development of wasteland.`
  line
  line `11. FISHERIES:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of fish seed production and distribution;`
  line
  line `(ii) development of pisiculture in private and community tanks;`
  line
  line `(iii) development of inland fisheries;`
  line
  line `(iv) promotion of fish curing and drying;`
  line
  line `(v) assistance to traditional fishing;`
  line
  line `(vi) organising fish marketing co-operatives; and`
  line
  line `(vii) welfare schemes for the uplift and development of fisherman.`
  line
  line `12. HOUSEHOLD INDUSTRIES:`
  line
  line `(including food processing):`
  line
  line `(i) identification of traditional skills in the locality and promotion of household industries;`
  line
  line `(ii) organisation of training programme for craftsmen and artisan;`
  line
  line `(iii) liaison to tap bank credit for household industries;`
  line
  line `(iv) popularising and marketing of finished products; and`
  line
  line `(v) organising khadi, handloom, handicraft and village and cottage industries.`
  line
  line `13. RURAL ROADS AND INLAND WATERWAYS:`
  line
  line `(i) construction and maintenance of roads other than National, State Highways and other`
  line `District road;`
  line
  line `(ii) bridges and culverts coming under roads falling in item (i);`
  line
  line `(iii) construction and maintenance of office buildings of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(iv) identification of major link roads connecting markets, educational institutions, health`
  line `centres; and`
  line
  line `(v) organising voluntary surrender of lands for new roads and for widening of existing roads.`
  line
  line `14. HEALTH AND HYGIENE:`
  line
  line `(i) implementation of immunization and vaccination programme;`
  line
  line `(ii) health education activities in hospitals, primary health centres and dispensaries;`
  line
  line `(iii) maternity and child health service activities;`
  line
  line `(iv) family welfare activities;`
  line
  line `(v) organising health camps with Gram Panchayats; and`
  line
  line `(vi) measures against environment pollution.`
  line
  line `15. RURAL HOUSING:`
  line
  line `(i) identification of houseless families;`
  line
  line `(ii) implementation of house building programmes in the district; and`
  line
  line `(iii) popularising low cost housing.`
  line
  line `16. EDUCATION:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of educational activities including the establishment and maintenance of`
  line `primary and secondary schools;`
  line
  line `(ii) planning of programmes for Adult Education and Library facilities;`
  line
  line `(iii) propagation of technical training and vocational education; and`
  line
  line `(iv) extension work for propagation of Science and Technology to rural areas.`
  line
  line `17. SOCIAL WELFARE AND WELFARE OF WEAKER SECTIONS AND HANDICAPPED`
  line `PERSONS:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of social welfare programme and social welfare activities with emphasis on`
  line `handicapped and mentally retarded persons;`
  line
  line `(ii) organising nursery schools, balwadies, night schools and libraries to eradicate illiteracy`
  line `and impart general education; and`
  line
  line `(iii) organising co-operative societies of Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `18. POVERTY ALLEVIATION PROGRAMMES:`
  line
  line `planning, supervision monitoring and implementation of poverty alleviation programmes.`
  line
  line `19. DRINKING WATER:`
  line
  line `(i) construction, repair and maintenance of drinking water wells, tanks and ponds;`
  line
  line `(ii) prevention and control of water pollution.`
  line
  line `20. RURAL ELECTRIFICATION:`
  line
  line `(i) promote extension of electricity to unelectrified areas;`
  line
  line `(ii) help in the prevention of illegal tapping of electricity; and`
  line
  line `(iii) help in the recovery and collection of electricity dues.`
  line
  line `21. NON-CONVENTIONAL ENERGY SOURCES:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion and development of non-conventional energy scheme; and`
  line
  line `(ii) propagation of efficient energy devices.`
  line
  line `22. SOCIAL REFORM ACTIVITIES:`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of women's organisation and welfare;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion of children's organisation and welfare;`
  line
  line `(iii) organise cultural and recreation activities;`
  line
  line `(iv) encouragement of sports and games and construction of rural stadia;`
  line
  line `(v) promotion of thrift and savings through:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of saving habits;`
  line
  line `(b) small savings campaign;`
  line
  line `(c) fight against spurious money lending practices and rural indebtedness.`
  line
  line `(4) In addition, the Zilla Parishad may-`
  line
  line `(a) manage or maintain any work of public utility or any institution vested in it or under its`
  line `control and management;`
  line
  line `(b) acquire and maintain village hats and markets;`
  line
  line `(c) make grants to Gram Panchayats;`
  line
  line `(d) adopt measures for the relief of people in distress;`
  line
  line `(e) co-ordinate and integrate the development plans and schemes prepared by Gram Panchayats in`
  line `the district;`
  line
  line `(f) examine and sanction the budget estimates of Gram Panchayat in the district;`
  line
  line `(g) undertake or execute any scheme extending to the whole or part of the district; and`
  line
  line `(h) take over the maintenance and control of any rural bridge, tank, ghat, well, channel or drain,`
  line `belonging to a private owner or any other authority on such terms as may be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(5) The Zilla Parishads of two or more adjacent districts may jointly undertake and execute any`
  line `development scheme on such terms and conditions as may be mutually agreed upon:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, by notification and subject to such conditions as it may impose,`
  line `transfer additional functions to the Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (42752)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `General powers of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42752&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the general or special orders of the`
  line `Government, the Zilla Parishad may--`
  line
  line `(a) incur expenditure on education or medical relief outside its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) provide for carrying out any work or measure likely to promote health, safety, education,`
  line `comfort, convenience or social or economic or cultural well-being of the inhabitants of the district;`
  line
  line `(c) contribute to association of All India, State or Inter-State level concerned with the promotion`
  line `of local government and for holding exhibition, seminar and conferences within the district related to`
  line `the activities of Gram Panchayat and Zilla Parishad; and`
  line
  line `(d) render financial or other assistance to any person for carrying in the district any activity which`
  line `is related to any of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Zilla Parishad shall have powers to do all acts necessary for or incidental to the carrying out`
  line `of the functions entrusted or delegated to it and, in particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `powers to exercise all powers specified under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (42753)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Assignment of functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42753&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may assign to Zilla Parishad, functions in`
  line `relation to any matters to which the executive authority of the Government extends or in respect of`
  line `functions which have been assigned to the State Government by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may, by notification, withdraw or modify the functions assigned under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (42754)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42754&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The Zilla Parishad may, by notification, delegate to the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer or other Officer any of the powers conferred by or under this Act on the Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (42755)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Standing Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42755&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Zilla Parishad shall have the following Standing Committees,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) General Standing Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) Finance, Audit and Planning Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) Social Justice Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) Education and Health Committee;`
  line
  line `(e) Agriculture and Industries Committee; and`
  line
  line `(f) Works Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Standing Committee shall consist of such number of members not exceeding five including`
  line `the Chairman elected by the members of Zilla Parishad from amongst the elected members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adhyaksha shall be the ex officio member and Chairman of the General Standing Committee`
  line `and the Finance, Audit and Planning Committee. The Up-Adhyaksha shall be the ex officio member and`
  line `Chairman of the Social Justice Committee. The other Standing Committee shall elect the Chairman from`
  line `among their members.`
  line
  line `(4) No member of the Zilla Parishad shall be eligible to serve not more than two Standing`
  line Committees.
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Executive Officer shall be the ex officio Secretary of the General Standing Committee`
  line `and the Finance, Audit and Planning Committee and he shall nominate one of the Deputy Secretaries as`
  line `ex officio Secretary for each of the remaining Standing Committees. The Chief Executive Officer shall be`
  line `entitled to attend the meetings of all the Standing Committees.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (42756)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Functions of the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42756&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The General Standing Committee shall perform`
  line `functions relating to the establishment matters and functions relating to communication, buildings, rural`
  line `housing, village extensions, relief against the natural calamities and allied matters and all other matters.`
  line
  line `(2) The Finance, Audit and Planning Committee shall perform the functions relating to:--`
  line
  line `(a) the finances of the Zilla Parishad, framing of Budgets, scrutinising proposals for increase of`
  line `revenue, examination of receipts and expenditure statements, consideration of all proposals affecting`
  line `the finances of the Zilla Parishad and general supervision, of the revenue and expenditure of the Zilla`
  line Parishad;
  line
  line `(b) the plan priorities, allocation of outlays to developments, horizontal and vertical linkages,`
  line `implementation of guidelines issued by the Government, regular review of planning programmes,`
  line `evaluation of important programmes and small savings schemes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Social Justice Committee shall perform functions relating to:--`
  line
  line `(a) promotion of education, economic, social, cultural and other interests of the Scheduled Castes,`
  line `Scheduled Tribes and Backward Classes;`
  line
  line `(b) protecting them from social injustice and all other forms of exploitation;`
  line
  line `(c) amelioration, of the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and Backward Classes;`
  line
  line `(d) securing social justice to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, women and other`
  line `weaker sections of the society.`
  line
  line `(4) The Education and Health Committee shall:--`
  line
  line `(a) be incharge of all educational activities of the Zilla. Parishad;`
  line
  line `(b) undertake the planning of education in the district within the framework of the national policy`
  line `and the national and state plans;`
  line
  line `(c) survey and evaluate the educational activities of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(d) perform such other duties pertaining to education, adult literacy and cultural activities as the`
  line `Zilla Parishad may assign to it;`
  line
  line `(e) health services, hospitals, water supply, family welfare and other related matters.`
  line
  line `(5) The Agriculture and Industry Committee shall perform functions relating to:--`
  line
  line `(a) agricultural production, animal husbandry, co-operation, contour bunding and reclamation;`
  line
  line `(b) village and cottage industries; and`
  line
  line `(c) promotion of industrial development of the district.`
  line
  line `(6) The Works Committee shall perform functions relating to maintenance of:--`
  line
  line `(a) roads including district roads, bridges, culverts;`
  line
  line `(b) maintenance of buildings under its control or transferred by the Government or any public`
  line `authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) maintenance of boats, ferries, waterways.`
  line
  line `(7) The Standing Committee referred to in sub-sections (1) to (6) shall perform the functions referred`
  line `to above to the extent the powers are delegated to them by the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(8) The Standing Committees shall perform in respect of matters assigned to them such additional`
  line `duties as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (42757)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Procedure of Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42757&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Zilla Parishad may frame regulations relating to election of`
  line `members of committees, conduct of business therein, and all other matters relating to the committees.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of every Standing Committee shall in respect of the work of that committee be`
  line `entitled to call for any information, return statement or report from the officer of the Zilla Parishad and to`
  line `enter on and inspect any immovable property of the Zilla Parishad or any work in progress concerning the`
  line committee.
  line
  line `(3) Each Standing Committee shall be entitled to require attendance at its meetings of any officer of`
  line `the Zilla Parishad who is connected with the work of the Committee. The Chief Executive Officer shall`
  line `under instruction of the committee, issue notices and secure the attendance of the officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (42758)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Power to acquire, hold and dispose of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42758&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Zilla Parishad shall have the power to`
  line `acquire, hold and dispose of property and to enter into contracts:`
  line
  line `Provided that in all cases of acquisition or disposal of immovable property the Zilla Parishad shall`
  line `obtain the previous approval of the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All roads, buildings or other works constructed by a Zilla Parishad with its own funds shall vest in`
  line it.
  line
  line `(3) The Government may allocate to a Zilla Parishad any public property situated within its`
  line `jurisdiction, and thereupon such property shall vest in the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a Zilla Parishad requires land to carry out any of the purposes of this Act, it may negotiate`
  line `with the person or persons having in the said land, and if it fails to reach an agreement, it may make an`
  line `application to the Deputy Commissioner for the acquisition of the land and the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `may, if he is satisfied that the land is required for a public purpose, take steps to acquire the land under`
  line `the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894) and such land shall on acquisition, vest in`
  line `the Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (42759)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Zilla Parishad Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42759&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every Zilla Parishad there shall be constituted a Zilla Parishad`
  line `Fund bearing the name of the Zilla Parishad and there shall be placed to the credit thereof:--`
  line
  line `(a) contributions and grants, if any, made by the Central or the State Government including such`
  line `part of land revenue collected in the State as may be determined by the Government;`
  line
  line `(b) contributions and grants, if any, made by a Gram Panchayat or any other local authority;`
  line
  line `(c) loans, if any, granted by the Central or State Government or raised by the Zilla Parishad on`
  line `security of its assets;`
  line
  line `(d) the proceeds of road-cess and public works-cess levied in the district;`
  line
  line `(e) all receipts on account of tolls, rates and fees levied by the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(f) all receipts in respect of any schools, hospitals, dispensaries, buildings, institutions or works,`
  line `vested in, constructed by or placed under the control and management of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(g) all sums received as gift or contribution and all income from any trust or endowment made in`
  line `favour of Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(h) such fines or penalties imposed and realised under the provisions of this Act or of the`
  line `bye-laws made thereunder, as may be, prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(i) all other sums received by or on behalf of the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Zilla Parishad shall set apart and apply annually such sum as may be required to meet the`
  line `cost of its own administration including the payment of salary, allowances, provident fund and gratuity to`
  line `the officers and employees. The overall expenditure on establishment shall not exceed one-third of the`
  line `total expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Zilla Parishad shall have the power to spend such sums as it thinks fit for carrying out the`
  line `purpose of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Zilla Parishad Fund shall be vested in the Zilla Parishad and the amount standing to the credit`
  line `of the fund shall be kept in such custody or invested in such manner as the Government may, from time to`
  line `time, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (42760)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title Taxation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42760&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such maximum rates as the Government prescribe, a Zilla Parishad`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) levy tolls on persons, vehicles or animals or any class of them at any toll-bar established by it`
  line `on any road other than kutcha road or any bridge vested in it or under its management;`
  line
  line `(b) levy tolls in respect for any ferry established by it or under its management;`
  line
  line `(c) levy road cess and public works cess;`
  line
  line `(d) levy the following fees and rates, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) fees on the registration of boats or vehicles;`
  line
  line `(ii) a fee for providing sanitary facilities at such places or pilgrimage, fairs and melas within`
  line `its jurisdiction as may be specified by the Government by notification;`
  line
  line `(iii) a fee for licence for fair or mela;`
  line
  line `(iv) a lighting rate where arrangement for lighting of public streets and places is made by the`
  line `Zilla Parishad within its jurisdiction; and`
  line
  line `(v) water rate, where arrangement for the supply of water for drinking, irrigation or any other`
  line `purpose is made by the Zilla Parishad within its jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The Zilla Parishad shall not undertake registration of any vehicle or levy fee thereof and shall not`
  line `provide sanitary arrangements at places of worship or pilgrimage, fairs and melas within its jurisdiction or`
  line `levy fee thereof if such vehicle has already been registered by any other authority under any law for the,`
  line `time being in force or if such provision for sanitary arrangement has already been made by any other local`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(3) The scales of tolls, fees or rates and the terms and conditions for the imposition thereof shall be`
  line `such as may be provided by regulation. Such regulation may provide for exemption from all or any of the`
  line `tolls, fees or rates in any class of cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (42761)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Financial arrangements of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42761&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Zilla Parishad may, subject to the provisions`
  line `of any law relating to the raising of loans by local authorities for the time being in force, raise from time`
  line `to time, with the approval of the Government, loans for the purpose of the Act and create a sinking fund`
  line `for the repayment of such loans.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) a Zilla Parishad may borrow money from`
  line `the Government or, with the previous sanction, of the Government, from banks or other financial`
  line `institutions, for furtherance of its objective on the basis of specific scheme as may be drawn up by the`
  line `Zilla Parishad for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (42762)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42762&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Zilla Parishad shall, at such time and in such manner as may be prescribed,`
  line `prepare in each year a budget of its estimated receipts and disbursements for the following year and`
  line `submit it to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may, within such time as may be prescribed either approve the budget or return`
  line `it to the Zilla Parishad for such modifications as it may direct. On such modifications being made the`
  line `budget shall be resubmitted within such time as may be prescribed for approval of the Government. If the`
  line `approval of the Government is not received by the Zilla Parishad by the last date of the financial year, the`
  line `budget shall be deemed to be approved by the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No expenditure shall be incurred unless the budget is approved by the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Zilla Parishad may prepare in each year a supplementary estimate providing for any`
  line `modification of its budget and may submit it to the Government for approval within such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (42763)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title Accounts.
  content `A Zilla Parishad shall keep accounts in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42763&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (42764)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42764&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) The audit of the accounts of the Zilla Parishad shall be carried out by the authority as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Government and a copy of the audit note shall be forwarded to the Zilla`
  line `Parishad within one month of the completion of the audit.`
  line
  line `(2) on receipt of the audit report referred to in sub-section (1), the Zilla Parishad shall either remedy`
  line `any defects or irregularities which have been pointed out in the audit and send to the Government within`
  line `three months an intimation of its having done so or shall, within the said period, supply any further`
  line `explanation to the prescribed authority in regard to such defects or irregularities as it is required to`
  line furnish.
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (42765)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Staff of Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42765&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) An officer of the rank of the Deputy Commissioner shall be the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer of the Zilla Parishad who shall be appointed by the Government. The`
  line `Government may, also appoint an Additional Chief Executive Officer for a Zilla Parishad on such terms`
  line `and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government shall also appoint a Chief Accounts Officer and a Chief Planning Officer for`
  line `each Zilla Parishad on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government shall post from time to time in every Zilla Parishad such number of officers of`
  line `Group A, B and C services of the State (including any officers appointed to such service from amongst`
  line `person employed by the existing local authority) and officers of an All India Service allocated to serve`
  line `under the Government, as the Government considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force the`
  line `Government or any other officer or other authority authorised by it in this behalf shall have the power to`
  line `effect transfer of the officers and officials so posted from one district to another district.`
  line
  line `(5) The Government may constitute, from such date as is specified, such services for each Zilla`
  line `Parishad as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (42766)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Functions of the Chief Executive Officer and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42766&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided by or under this Act, the Chief Executive Officer shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) carry out the policies and directions of the Zilla Parishad and take necessary measures for the`
  line `speedy execution of all works and developmental schemes of Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(b) discharge the duties imposed upon him, by or under this Act or the rules and regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(c) control the officers and servants of the Zilla Parishad subject to the general superintendence`
  line `and control of the Zilla Adhyaksha and under such rules as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) have custody of all papers and documents relating to Zilla Parishad; and`
  line
  line `(e) draw and disburse money out of the Zilla Parishad Funds and exercise such other powers and`
  line `perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer shall attend every meeting of the Zilla Parishad and may take part in`
  line `the discussion but shall not have the right to move any resolution or to vote. If in the opinion of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer any proposal before the Zilla Parishad is violative of or is inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any other law or the rules made thereunder, it shall be his duty to bring the same`
  line `to the notice of the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Accounts Officer shall advise the Zilla Parishad in matters of financial policy and shall`
  line `be responsible for all matters relating to the accounts of the Zilla Parishad including preparation of`
  line `accounts and the budget.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Accounts Officer shall ensure that no expenditure is incurred except under proper`
  line `sanction and in accordance with this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder and shall disallow`
  line `any expenditure not warranted by the Act or rules and regulations or for which no provision is made in`
  line `the budget.`
  line
  line `(5) The Additional Chief Executive Officer shall assist the Chief Executive Officer in the`
  line `performance of his duties.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Planning Officer shall advise the Zilla Parishad in matters of plan formulation and shall`
  line `be responsible for all matters relating to planning of the Zilla Parishad including the preparation of plans`
  line `of economic development and social justice and annual plan of the district.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (42767)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Right to requisition records, recover money, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42767&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person in possession of money,`
  line `accounts, records or other property pertaining to a Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad shall on the`
  line `requisition in writing of the Chief Executive Officer for this purpose, forthwith hand over such money or`
  line `deliver up such accounts, records or other property to the Chief Executive Officer or the person`
  line `authorised in the requisition to receive the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer may also take steps to recover any money due by such person in the`
  line `same manner and subject to the same provisions as in the relevent Land Revenue Act, for the recovery of`
  line `the arrears of land revenue from defaulters and for the purpose of requisitioning the accounts, records or`
  line `for recovering any other property apertaining to the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad may issue a search`
  line `warrant and exercise all such powers with respect thereto as may lawfully be exercised by a Magistrate`
  line `under the provisions of Chapter VII of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) Every person knowing where any money, accounts, records or other property apertaining to a`
  line `Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad are concealed shall be bound to give information of the same to the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal shall lie from an order of the Chief Executive Officer under this section to the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (42768)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Powers to revise or modify decisions of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42768&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Every Gram Panchayat and every Zilla`
  line `Parishad shall have power to revise or modify any decision taken by any of its committees.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (42769)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Powers of Gram Panchayats to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42769&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Gram Panchayat may, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and with the previous sanction of the Zilla Parishad`
  line `make bye-laws to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In making any bye-laws under sub-section (1) the Gram Panchayat may provide that a`
  line `contravention thereof shall be punishable with such fine as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such bye-law may also provide that a person contravening the same shall be required to`
  line `remedy so far as it lies in his power, the mischief, if any, caused by such contravention.`
  line
  line `(4) All bye-laws made under this section shall be subject to the condition of previous publication and`
  line `such publication shall be in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (42770)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Powers of Zilla Parishad to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42770&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Zilla Parishad may subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and with the previous sanction of the Government,`
  line `by notification, make regulations to carry out the purposes of this Act in so far as it relates to its powers`
  line `and duties.`
  line
  line `(2) The regulations made under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication and such publication shall be in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (42771)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Powers of Government to make model regulations and bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42771&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and after previous publication of the`
  line `draft for not less than one month, make model regulations and bye-laws for Zilla Parishads and Gram`
  line `Panchayats respectively.`
  line
  line `(2) A Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad may by resolution adopt the model bye-laws or regulations,`
  line `as the case may be, made under sub-section (1), and such bye-laws and regulations shall come into force`
  line `within the jurisdiction of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad from such date as the Gram Panchayat or`
  line `Zilla Parishad as the case may be, may specify in a notice published in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (42801)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Powers of Government to dissolve and reconstitute Gram Panchayat and Zilla Parishad in case of alteration of area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42801&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) When on account of the reason that the limits of an area of Gram`
  line `Panchayat or Zilla Parishad, are altered, the Government may by order published in the Official Gazette`
  line `dissolve such Panchayat or Parishad, from a date, specified in the order and direct that Gram Panchayat or`
  line `Zilla Parishad concerned:--`
  line
  line `(i) be reconstituted for the Panchayat area of which the Gram Panchayat or the district of which`
  line `Zilla Parishad has been dissolved; or`
  line
  line `(ii) be established for a Panchayat area, or district which has been newly constituted.`
  line
  line `(2) The members of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad which has been dissolved under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall vacate their office from the date specified in the order of the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad reconstituted or established under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall consist of members nominated by the Government and such members shall as far as`
  line `practicable be persons who are members of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad which has been`
  line `dissolved under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairpersons of Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad shall be elected in the manner provided in`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad so reconstituted or established shall be for such`
  line `period not exceeding six months as the Government shall by order specify.`
  line
  line `(6) Before the expiry of the term of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad constituted in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section (5), a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad shall be constituted in the`
  line `manner provided under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the remainder of the period for which the dissolved Gram Panchayat or Zilla`
  line `Parishad would have continued is less than six months it shall not be necessary to hold an election under`
  line `this section for constituting a Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad for such period.`
  line
  line `(7) A Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad constituted under sub-section (1) shall continue only for the`
  line `remainder of the period for which the dissolved Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad would have continued`
  line `had it not been so dissolved.`
  line
  line `(8) When a Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad has been dissolved and reconstituted or established`
  line `under this section so much of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad fund and other property vesting in the`
  line `Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad which has been dissolved shall vest in and such portion of the debts,`
  line `and obligations shall be transferred to, the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad reconstituted or established`
  line `under this section as the Government may direct by an order made in writing.`
  line
  line `(9) The rights and liabilities of the dissolved Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad in respect of civil and`
  line `criminal proceedings, contracts, agreements and other matters or things arising in and relating to any part`
  line `of the area subject to the authority of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad reconstituted or established`
  line `shall vest in such Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(10) Any appointment, notification, notice, tax, order, scheme, licence, permission, rule, regulation or`
  line `form made, issued, imposed or granted by the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad which has been`
  line `dissolved in respect of any part of the area subject to the authority of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla`
  line `Parishad which has been reconstituted or established, shall be deemed to have been made, issued,`
  line `imposed or granted by such Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad unless and until it is suspended by any`
  line `appointment, notification, notice, form, order, scheme, licence, permission, rule and regulation made,`
  line `issued, imposed or granted by such Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (42773)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Dissolution of Gram Panchayats and Zilla Parishad in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42773&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the`
  line `opinion of the Zilla Parishad, a Gram Panchayat exceed or abuses its powers or is not competent to`
  line `perform or makes persistent default in the performance of the duties imposed on it under this Act or any`
  line
  line `other law for the time being in force, the Zilla Parishad may by order published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `dissolve such Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) If in the opinion of the Government, a Zilla Parishad exceeds or abuses its powers or is not`
  line `competent to perform or makes persistent default in the performance of the duties imposed on it under`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the Government may, by an order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, dissolve such Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(3) Before publishing an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) the Zilla Parishad or the`
  line `Government shall communicate to the Gram Panchayat or to the Zilla Parishad, as the case may be, the`
  line `grounds on which it proposes to do so, and fix a reasonable period for the Panchayat concerned to show`
  line `cause against the proposal and consider its explanation and objections, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) When a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad is dissolved all the members of Gram Panchayat or`
  line `Zilla Parishad shall, from the date specified in the order, vacate their office as such members.`
  line
  line `(5) If a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad is dissolved:--`
  line
  line `(a) all the powers and duties of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad shall, during the period of`
  line `its dissolution be exercised and performed by such person or persons as the Zilla Parishad or the`
  line `Government, as the case may be, may from time to time, appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) all property vested in the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad shall during the period of`
  line `dissolution vest in the Zilla Parishad or the Government, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(c) the person is vacating office on dissolution shall be eligible for re-election.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (42774)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Inquiry into the afffairs of the Panchayats by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42774&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, at`
  line `any time for reasons to be recorded in writing, cause any inquiry to be made by any of its officers in`
  line `regard to any Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad on matters concerning it, or any matters with respect to`
  line `which the sanction, approval, consent or orders of the Government is required under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Officer holding such inquiry shall have the powers of the Civil Court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) to take evidence and to compel attendance of witnesses and production of`
  line `documents for the purposes of the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may make orders as to costs of inquiries made under sub-section (1) and as to`
  line `the parties by whom and the funds out of which they shall be paid and such order may, on the application`
  line `of the Commissioner or of any person named therein be executed as if it were a decree of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (42775)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Inspection of Development Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42775&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of efficient and economical`
  line `execution of any works or development schemes undertaken by a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad an`
  line `officer or person authorised by general or special order of the Government, if he considers it necessary to`
  line `give technical guidance or assistance to any officer of or under the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad who`
  line `is charged with the execution or maintenance of any such work or development scheme, then the officer`
  line `or person so authorised may periodically inspect such works or development schemes to give such`
  line `guidance, assistance or advise as he thinks necessary in relation to such works or development schemes`
  line `and shall forward to the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad a report on the inspection made pointing out`
  line `therein any irregularities noticed, and suggestions for improvement.`
  line
  line `(2) In implementation of the plans or schemes all the rules applicable to Government Departments`
  line `such as for purchase, tender, quality control, technical sanctions, accounts and audit and supervision shall`
  line `mutatis mutandis be applicable in case of a Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (42776)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Directions from the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42776&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act it shall`
  line `be lawful for the Government to issue directions to any Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad in matters`
  line `relating to State and National Policies and such directions shall be binding on the Gram Panchayat or`
  line `Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may:--`
  line
  line `(a) call for any record, register or any other document in possession under the control of any`
  line `Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(b) require any Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad to furnish in return, plan, estimate, statement,`
  line `account or statistics; and`
  line
  line `(c) require any Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad to furnish any information or report on any`
  line `matter connected with such Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (42802)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Commissioner and Chief Executive officers powers in respect of Gram Panchayat and Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42802&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer may in respect of Gram Panchayat exercise the`
  line `following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) call for proceedings of any Gram Panchayat or any extract of any book or document in the`
  line `possession of or under the control of the Gram Panchayat or any return or statement of account or`
  line report;
  line
  line `(b) require a Gram Panchayat, to take into consideration any objection which appears to him to`
  line `exist to the doing of anything which is about to be done or is being done by such Gram Panchayat or`
  line `any information which appears to him to necessitate the doing of anything by such Gram Panchayat`
  line `or within such period as he may fix;`
  line
  line `(c) order a duty to be performed within a specified period if a Gram Panchayat has made default`
  line `in the performance of any duty and if such duty is not performed within the specified period, to`
  line `appoint a person to perform such duty and direct that the expenses thereof shall be paid by the`
  line `defaulting Gram Panchayat within such period as he may fix;`
  line
  line `(d) direct a Gram Panchayat to levy any tax if it has failed to do so in accordance with the`
  line `provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) call for meetings of the Gram Panchayat, or any of its committees if no meeting of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat or its committees has been held in accordance with the provisions of this Act or rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Panchayat may appeal to the Commissioner, against any order made under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) by the Chief Executive Officer within thirty days from the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may in respect of Zilla Parishad exercise the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) call for proceedings of any Zilla Parishad or any extract of any book or document in the`
  line `possession of or under the control of the Zilla Parishad or any return or statement of account or`
  line report;
  line
  line `(b) require a Zilla Parishad, to take into consideration any objection which appears to him to exist`
  line `to the doing of anything which is about to be done or is being done by such Zilla Parishad or any`
  line `information which appears to him to necessitate the doing of anything by such Zilla Parishad or`
  line `within such period as he may fix;`
  line
  line `(c) order a duty to be performed within a specified period if a Zilla Parishad has made default in`
  line `the performance of any duty and if such duty is not performed within the specified period, to appoint`
  line `a person to perform such duty and direct that the expenses thereof shall be paid by the defaulting Zilla`
  line `Parishad within such period as he may fix;`
  line
  line `(d) call for meetings of the Zilla Parishad or any of its committees if no meeting of the Zilla`
  line `Parishad or its committees has been held in accordance with the provisions of this Act or rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(4) The Zilla Parishad may appeal to the Government, against any order made under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) by the Commissioner, within thirty days from the date of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (42803)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power of Government and Chief Executive Officer to provide for performance of duties in default of Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42803&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `When the Government in case of a Zilla Parishad and`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer in case of a Gram Panchayat is informed on complaint made or otherwise,`
  line `that any Zilla Parishad or Gram Panchayat has made default in performing any duty imposed on it, by or`
  line `under this Act, or by or under any law for the time being in force and if the Government or Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, as the case may be, is satisfied after due enquiry that any Zilla Parishad or Gram`
  line
  line `Panchayat, has failed in the performance of such duty, the Government or the Chief Executive Officer, as`
  line `the case may be, may fix a period for the performance of that duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such period shall be fixed unless the Zilla Parishad or Gram Panchayat concerned`
  line `has been given an opportunity to show cause why such an order shall not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (42779)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Zilla Prishads, power of suspending the executions of order, etc., of Gram Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42779&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `If in the opinion of the Zilla Parishad the execution of any order or resolution of a Gram Panchayat or any`
  line `order of any authority or Officer of a Gram Panchayat or the doing anything which is about to be done, or`
  line `is being done, by or on behalf of a Gram Panchayat is unjust, unlawful, improper or is causing or is likely`
  line `to cause injury or annoyance to the public or to lead to a breach of the peace, it may by order suspend the`
  line `execution of or prohibit the doing thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Zilla Parishad makes an order under sub-section (1) it shall forthwith forward to the`
  line `Government and to the Gram Panchayat affected thereby a copy of the order with a statement of the`
  line `reasons for making it and it shall be in the discretion of the Government to confirm or resind the order or`
  line `to direct that it shall continue to be in force with or without modification permanently or for such period`
  line `as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of the Zilla Parishad made under this section shall be confirmed, revised or`
  line `modified by the Government without giving the Gram Panchayat reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against the said order.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (42780)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Government’s power of suspending execution of unlawful orders or resolutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42780&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) If on`
  line `the receipt of a report from the Chief Executive Officer in this behalf or otherwise the Government is of`
  line `the opinion that execution of any order or resolution of Zilla Parishad or the doing of anything which is`
  line `about to be done or is being done by on behalf of a Zilla Parishad is unjust, unlawful, or improper or is`
  line `causing or is likely to cause injury or annoyance to the public or to lead to a breach of the peace, it may,`
  line `by an order suspend the execution or prohibit the doing thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Government makes an order under sub-section (1), it shall forthwith forward to the Zilla`
  line `Parishad affected thereby a copy of the order with a statement of reasons for making it and the`
  line `Government may confirm or rescind the order or direct that it shall continue to be in force with or without`
  line `modification permanently or for such period as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made by the Government without giving the`
  line `Zilla Parishad concerned a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the said order.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (42781)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Purchase of stores and equipment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42781&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may by general or special order`
  line `provide for all any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which purchase of stores, equipments, machineries and other articles required`
  line `by the Zilla Parishad or Gram Panchayat shall be made by them;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which tender for works, contracts and supplies shall be invited and examined`
  line `and accepted by the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which works, and development schemes may be executed and inspected and`
  line `payment may be made in respect of such works an schemes; and`
  line
  line `(d) constitution of committee for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise expressly provided in sub-section (1), in respect of all other matters relating to`
  line `withdrawal of funds, form of bills, incurring of expenditure maintenance of accounts, rendering of`
  line `accounts and such other matters, the rules, of implementation as applicable to Departments of the`
  line `Government shall mutatis mutandis apply in case of a Gram Panchayat and Zilla Parishad.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (42782)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power to appoint administrator in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42782&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever,--`
  line
  line `(a) any general election to a Zilla Parishad under this Act or any proceedings consequent thereon`
  line `has been stayed by an order of a competent court, or authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) all the members or more than two-thirds of the members of a Zilla Parishad have resigned,`
  line
  line `the Government shall by notification in the Official Gazette appoint an Administrator for such period as`
  line `may be specified in the notification and may, by like notification, curtail or extend the period of such`
  line `appointment, so however, that the total period of such appointment shall not exceed six months.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, on the appointment of an Administrator under`
  line `sub-section (1) the Zilla Parishad and the Committees thereof and the Adhyaksha, or Up-Adhyaksha of`
  line `such Zilla Parishad charged with carrying out the provisions of this Act, or any other law, shall cease to`
  line `exercise any powers and perform and discharge any duties or functions conferred or imposed on them by`
  line `or under this Act or any other law and all such powers shall be exercised and all such duties and functions`
  line `shall be performed and discharged by the Administrator during the period of such appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (42783)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Removal of members for misconduct, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42783&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `The Government if it thinks fit on the`
  line `recommendation of the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad or otherwise, may remove any member after`
  line `giving him an opportunity of being heard and after such enquiry as it deems necessary if such members`
  line `has been guilty of misconduct in the discharge of his duties or of any disgraceful conduct or has become`
  line `incapable of performing his duties as a member`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (42784)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Restrictions on withdrawal of powers and functions from the Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42784&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the transfer of any power, functions and duties in respect of any matter to a Panchayat`
  line `under this Act the Government on a proposal from Panchayat in that behalf or where it is satisfied that by`
  line `reason of a change in the nature of the matter such as the conversion of a primary health centre into a`
  line `secondary health centre or hospital or the conversion of a seed multiplication farm into an agricultural`
  line `research farm or a road becoming a part of a highway, the matter would cease to be a matter in relevant`
  line `Panchayat functions list and it is necessary to withdraw from the Panchayat powers, functions or duties in`
  line `respect of such matter, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, withdraw such powers, functions and`
  line `duties with effect from the date specified in the notification and make such incidental and consequential`
  line `orders as may be necessary to provide for matters including the taking over of the property, right and`
  line `liabilities, if any vesting in the Panchayat and of the staff, if any, which may have been transferred to the`
  line `Panchayat as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (42785)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Preparation of development plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42785&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Gram Panchayat shall prepare every year a`
  line `development plan and submit it to the Zilla Parishad before such date and in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Every Zilla Parishad shall prepare every year a development plan of the District after including`
  line `the development plans of the Gram Panchayat and submit it to the District Planning Committee`
  line `constituted under section 96 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (42786)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `District Planning Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42786&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government shall constitute in every district a District`
  line `Planning Committee to consolidate the plans prepared by the Zilla Parishad, Gram Panchayats, Nagar`
  line `Panchayat, Municipal Council and Municipal Corporation in the district and to prepare a draft`
  line `development plan for the district as a whole.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Planning Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) members of the House of the People who represent the whole or part of the district;`
  line
  line `(b) all the members or the State Legislative Assembly whose constituencies lie within the district;`
  line
  line `(c) Adhyaksha of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(d) Mayor or the President of the Municipal Corporation or the Municipal Council respectively,`
  line `having jurisdiction over the headquarters of the district; and`
  line
  line `(e) such number of persons not less than four-fifth of the total number of members of the`
  line `Committee as may be specified by the Government elected in the prescribed manner from amongst the`
  line `members of the Zilla Parishad, Nagar Panchayat and Councillors of the Municipal Corporation and the`
  line `Municipal Councils in the district, in proportion to the ratio between the population of the rural areas and`
  line `of the urban areas in the district.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman of the District Co-operative Banks and of the Land Development Bank shall be`
  line `permanent invitees of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officer shall be the Secretary of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Deputy Commissioner of the districts shall be the Chairman of the District Planning`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(6) The District Planning Committee shall consolidate the plans prepared by the Zilla Parishad, Gram`
  line `Panchayat, Nagar Panchayat, Municipal Council and the Municipal Corporations in the district and`
  line `prepare a draft development plan for the district as a whole.`
  line
  line `(7) Every District Planning Committee shall in preparing the draft development plan:--`
  line
  line `(a) have regard to--`
  line
  line `(i) the matters of common interest between the Zilla Parishad, Gram Panchayats, Nagar`
  line `Panchayats, Municipal Corporation and Municipal Councils in the district including spatial`
  line `planning sharing of water and other physical and natural resource, the integrated development of`
  line `infrastructure and environmental conservation,`
  line
  line `(ii) the extent and type of available resources whether financial or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) consult such institutions and organisations as the Government may by order specify.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chairman of every District Planning Committee shall forward the development plan, as`
  line `recommended by such Committee to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (42787)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Finance Commission for Panchyats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42787&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall constitute every five years a`
  line `Finance Commission to review the financial position of the Zilla Parishads and Gram Panchayats and to`
  line `make recommendations to the Government as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles which should govern--`
  line
  line `(i) the distribution between the State and the Zilla Parishads and the Gram Panchayats and the`
  line `net proceeds of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees leviable by the Government which may be divided`
  line `between them and allocation between the Zilla Parishad and Gram Panchayat of their respective`
  line `shares of such proceeds;`
  line
  line `(ii) the determination of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees which may be assigned to or`
  line `appropriated by the Zilla Parishad and Gram Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(iii) the grants-in-aid to the Zilla Parishads and Gram Panchayats from the Consolidated Fund`
  line `of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) the measures needed to improve the financial position of the Zilla Parishads and Gram`
  line `Panchayats; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter referred to the Finance Commission by the Governor in the interest of sound`
  line `finance of the Zilla Parishads and Gram Panchayats.`
  line
  line `(2) The Finance Commission shall consist of a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The member of Finance Commission shall be appointed in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `from among persons who--`
  line
  line `(a) have experience in public affairs; or`
  line
  line `(b) are or have been, or are qualified to be appointed as a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(c) have special knowledge of the finances and accounts of Governments; or`
  line
  line `(d) have had wide experience in financial matters and in administration; or`
  line
  line `(e) have special knowledge of economics.`
  line
  line `(4) The Finance Commission shall determine its procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) The member of the Finance Commission may resign his office by writing under his hand and`
  line `addressed to the Governor but he shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by the`
  line Governor.
  line
  line `(6) The casual vacancy occurring due to the resignation of the member under sub-section (5) or for`
  line `any other reason may be filled by fresh appointment and a member so appointed shall hold office for the`
  line `remaining period for which the member in whose place as he was appointed would have held office.`
  line
  line `(7) In the performance of its functions, the Commission shall have the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to call for any record from any officer or authority;`
  line
  line `(b) to summon any person to give evidence or produce records; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other powers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The Governor shall cause every recommendation made by the Finance Commission under this`
  line `section together with an explanatory memorandum as to the action taken thereon to be laid before the`
  line `State Legislature`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (42788)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `State Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42788&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a State Election Commission constituted by the`
  line `Government for superintendence, direction and control of the preparation of electoral rolls for, and the`
  line `conduct of all elections to the Panchayat bodies in the State under this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of a State Election Commissioner to be appointed by the Governor.`
  line
  line `(3) The conditions of services and tenure of office of the State Election Commissioner shall be such`
  line `as the Governor may by rule determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Election Commissioner shall not be removed from his office except in like`
  line `manner and on the like grounds as a Judge of the High Court and the conditions of service of the State`
  line `Election Commissioner shall not be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Government shall, when so requested by the State Election Commission, make available to`
  line `the State Election Commission such staff as may be necessary for the discharge of the functions conferred`
  line `on the State Election Commission under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (42789)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Determination of elected members after census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42789&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Upon the publication of the figures of each`
  line `Census, the number of elected members of a Panchayat shall be determined by the State Government on`
  line `the basis of the population of the Panchayat area as ascertained at that Census:`
  line
  line `Provided that the determination of the number as aforesaid shall not affect the then composition of the`
  line `Panchayats existing at the time of the publication of Census under this section until the expiry of its term.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (42790)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Qualification of membership for election to Panchayat or Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42790&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `Every person`
  line `whose name is in the list of voters within the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad constituency and is`
  line `ordinarily resident within the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad area shall, unless disqualified under this`
  line `Act or under any other law for the time being in force, be qualified to be elected as a member of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of seats reserved for the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes or Backward Classes and women, no person who is not a member of any of the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled`
  line `Tribes or Backward Classes or is not a women, as the case may be, shall be qualified to be elected to such`
  line seat.
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (42791)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Disqualification for memberships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42791&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen and`
  line `for being a member of a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he has not attained the age of twenty-one years;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is so disqualified by or under any law for the time being in force for the purposes of`
  line `elections to the State Legislatures;`
  line
  line `(c) if an order has been passed against him under section 117 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), in proceedings instituted under section 110 of the Code, such order not having been`
  line `subsequently revised or quashed; or`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been dismissed from the service under any local authority; or`
  line
  line `(e) if, having been a legal or medical practitioner or a chartered accountant, his name has been`
  line `removed from the rolls or he is suspended by order of a competent authority, the disqualification in`
  line `the latter case being operative during the period of such suspension; or`
  line
  line `(f) if he has been removed from membership of any local authority; or`
  line
  line `(g) if he holds any office of profit under any local or other authority subject to the control of the`
  line `Central Government, the State Government or the Government of any other State, other than such`
  line `offices as are declared by rules made under this Act not to disqualify the holder.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, a person shall not be deemed to hold any office of`
  line `profit under the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad by reason only that he is a Pradhan or Up-Pradhan`
  line `of the Gram Panchayat or an Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha of Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(h) if, save as hereinafter provided he has directly or indirectly any share or interest in any work`
  line `done by order of the Gram Panachayat or the Zilla Parishad or in any contract or employment with, or`
  line `under, or by, or on behalf of the Gram Panachayat or the Zilla Parishad; or`
  line
  line `(i) if he is employed as a paid legal practitioner on behalf of the Gram Panchayat or the Zilla`
  line `Parishad or accepts employments as legal practitioner against the Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad;`
  line or
  line
  line `(j) if arrears of any kind are due by him to the Gram Panchayat or the Zilla Parishad under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) the disqualification in clause (b) shall cease to operate after the expiry of the period during`
  line `which a person is ordered to furnish security;`
  line
  line `(b) the disqualification in clause (d) or clause (e) shall cease to operate after the expiry of five`
  line `years from the date of such sentence or dismissal, or disenrolment or earlier by an order of the`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) the disqualification in clause (f) shall cease to operate after the expiry of five years from the`
  line `date of such removal;`
  line
  line `(d) a person shall not be deemed to have incurred disqualification under clause (h) by reason of`
  line his,--
  line
  line `(i) having a share in any joint stock company or a share or interest in any association`
  line `registered under the Manipur Societies Registration Act, 1989 (1 of 1990) in any co-operative`
  line `society, which shall contract with or be employed by or on behalf of the Gram Panchayat or the`
  line `Zilla Parishad; or`
  line
  line `(ii) having a share or interest in any newspaper in which any advertisement relating to the`
  line `affairs of the Gram Panchayat or the Zilla Parishad is inserted; or`
  line
  line `(iii) holding a debenture or being otherwise concerned in any loan raised by or on behalf of`
  line `the Gram Panchayat or the Zilla Parishad.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether a member of a Panchayat at any level has become subject to`
  line `any of disqualification mentioned in sub-section (1), the question referred for the decision of Election`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(3) If a person who is chosen as a member of a Panchayat is or becomes Member of the House of the`
  line `People, the Council of States, the State Legislative Assembly or the State Legislative Council, or is or`
  line `becomes a Municipal Councillor or a Councillor of Municipal Corporation or a Member of a Sanitary`
  line
  line `Board, and other Panchayat, then within fifteen days from the date of commencement of the term of`
  line `office of a Member of the House of the People, the Council of States, the State Legislative Assembly or`
  line `State Legislative Council or of a Municipal Councillor or a Councillor of a Municipal Corporation or a`
  line `Member of such other Panchayat his seat in the Panchayat shall become vacant unless he has previously`
  line `resigned his seat in the House of the People, the Council of States, the State Legislative Assembly or the`
  line `State Legislative Council or the Municipal Corporation of the Board or such other Panchayat, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (42804)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Power of State Government to rescind or suspend resolution of a Gram Panchayat or Zilla Parishad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42804&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, within a period of six months, by order in writing, rescind`
  line `any resolution passed by a Gram Panchayat or a Zilla Parishad, if in its opinion such resolution--`
  line
  line `(a) has not been legally passed; or`
  line
  line `(b) is in excess, or abuse of the powers conferred by, or under this Act or in rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, before taking any such action under sub-section (1) give the Gram`
  line `Panchayat or the Zilla Parishad concerned an opportunity for making representation against the proposed`
  line order.
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (42793)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Constitution of Election Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42793&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government shall constitute Election Tribunal`
  line `consisting of one member to be appointed by that Government to dispose of:--`
  line
  line `(i) all election petitions challenging elections to a Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(ii) matters relating to disqualification of a member of the Panchayat; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other election matter,`
  line
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Headquarter of the Tribunal shall be at such place as may be notified.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Election Tribunal made under sub-section (1) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (42794)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Annual Administration Report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42794&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the first day of April in every`
  line `year and not later than such date as may be fixed by the Government, the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `Zilla Parishad shall prepare a report on the administration of the Zilla Parishad during the preceding year`
  line `in such form and with such details as the Government may direct and submit the report to the Zilla`
  line `Parishad. After approval by the Zilla Parishad the report shall be submitted to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The report submitted to the Government under sub-section (1) shall together with a memorandum`
  line `by the Government reviewing the working of the Zilla Parishad be laid before the House of the State`
  line Legislature.
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (42795)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42795&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification In the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for convening and holding the meetings of Gram Sabha under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner for publication of Electoral Rolls of Gram Panchayat and the authority competent`
  line `to publish the same as referred to in sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner for filing an appeal against the order of the authority publishing the Electoral Rolls`
  line `as referred to in sub-section (5) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the rotation of the reserved seats in constituencies of a Gram Panchayat under sub-sections (1)`
  line `and (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure for election of Pradhan and members of Gram Panchayat under section 21;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner for filling up the casual vacancies in Gram Panchayat referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 23;`
  line
  line `(g) the payment of honorarium and other allowances to Pradhan and Up-Pradhan under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(h) powers, functions and duties of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan as referred to in clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section (1) and clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(i) the authority competent to receive and accept the resignation of Pradhan and Up-Pradhan;`
  line
  line `(j) the officers to whom the notice of meeting of the Gram Panchayat is to be forwarded by the`
  line `Secretary under sub-section (3) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner for co-opting the members by Standing Committee under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(l) the custody in which Gram Panchayat fund shall be kept as referred to in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(m) the procedure for preparation and approval of the budget of Gram Panchayat under section`
  line `and maintenance of accounts and its audit under sections 43 and 44;`
  line
  line `(n) appointment, terms and conditions of service, pay and allowances and other service conditions`
  line `of the Secretary as referred to in section 45;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of election of members to Zilla Parishad under section 50;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner for filling up the casual vacancy in Zilla Parishad referred to in section 51;`
  line
  line `(q) the rotation of reserved seats in constituencies of Zilla Parishad under sub-sections (1) and (3)`
  line `of section 52;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner for reservation of seats of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha of Zilla Parishad`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(s) salary and allowances of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha and sitting fee and other allowances`
  line `to the members of Zilla Parishad under section 55;`
  line
  line `(t) powers, functions and duties of Adhyaksha and Up-Adhyaksha referred to in section 56;`
  line
  line `(u) the authority competent to receive and accept the resignation of Adhyaksha and`
  line `Up-Adhyaksha under sub-section (2) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(v) the additional duties to be performed by the Committees under sub-section (8) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(w) the maximum rate of taxes to be levied by a Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(x) preparation and approval of budget for Zilla Parishad under section 72;`
  line
  line `(y) maintenance of accounts of Zilla Parishad and their audit referred to in sections 73 and 74;`
  line
  line `(z) the terms and conditions for appointment of Additional Chief Executive Officer, Chief`
  line
  line `Accounts Officer, Chief Planning Officer and other staff members under section 75;`
  line
  line `(aa) the superintendence and control of the affairs of Zilla Parishad by the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer referred to in clauses (c) and (e) of sub-section (1) of section 76;`
  line
  line `(ab) the limits of fine to be imposed by Gram Panchayat under sub-section (2) of section 79 and`
  line `the manner of publication of bye-laws of Gram Panchayat under sub-section (4) of the said section;`
  line
  line `(ac) the manner for appointment of member of Finance Commission referred to in sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 97.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly while it is in session, for a total period of twenty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the successive sessions aforesaid, the House agrees in making modification in`
  line `the rule or that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or annulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (42796)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Bar to interference by Courts in electoral matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42796&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the validity of any law relating to the delimitation of constituencies or the allotment of seat to`
  line `such constituencies, made or purporting to be made under the relevant provision of the Constitution`
  line `of India shall not be called in question in any Court;`
  line
  line `(b) no election to any Panchayat shall be called in question in any Court`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (42797)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Taking of oath.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42797&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `Every member, Adhyaksha or Up-Adhyaksha of the Zilla Parishad and every`
  line `Member, Pradhan or Up-Pradhan of a Gram Panchayat shall before taking his seat, make at a meeting of`
  line `the Zilla Parishad or Gram Panchayat as the case may be, an oath or affirmation of his allegiance to the`
  line `Constitution of India in the following form, namely:--`
  line
  line `I,............................................................... being a Member/Adhyaksha/Up-Adhyaksha/Pradhan/`
  line `Up-Pradhan of the.................................... do swear in the name of God (or solemnly affirm) that I will`
  line `bear true faith and allegiance to the Constitution of India as by law established and that I will faithfully`
  line `discharge the duty upon which I am about to enter.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (42798)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42798&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1975 (Manipur Act 12 of 1975) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1975 (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `repealed Act) the repeal shall not affect:--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operations of the repealed Act or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the repealed`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed under the`
  line `repealed Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceedings or remedy in respect of such right, privilege, obligation,`
  line `liability, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid, and any such investigation, legal proceedings or`
  line `remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any such penalty, foreiture or punishment may`
  line `be imposed as if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (42799)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414&sectionId=42799&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_199426_1517807320414
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Government, may by order, published in the Official Gazette as the occasion may require, do anything`
  line `which appears to it to be necessary to remove the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
